flavorText: " . . . And the third little boar built his house out of rootwalla plates . . . ."
" . . . Cao Pi, Cao Rui, Fang, Mao, and briefly, Huan—  The Sima took the empire in their turn. . . ."
" . . . When the trees bow down their heads, The wind is passing by."
" . . . and you must also apply for an application license, file documents 136(iv) and 22-C and -D in triplicate, pay all requisite fees, request a . . ."
"'Air superiority?' Not while our archers scan the skies."
"'Davvol, blast those elves.' 'Davvol, transport those troops.' No one cares that today is my birthday."

"'Do you know, I always thought Unicorns were fabulous monsters, too? I never saw one alive before!' 'Well, now that we have seen each other,' said the Unicorn, 'if you'll believe in me, I'll believe in you.'"
"'Fraid of heights? Ride a horse. 'Fraid of missing out? Rein up a drake."
"'Here lies our beloved Gartu, the gentlest of all men.' Ooh, I love irony."
"'I have arrived,' bellowed Brawn, and the plane shuddered."

"'I'll show you how to handle the treefolk!' the giant bragged, and he strode off into the forest. Two days later he returned, his face masked in sap and a nest behind his ear. None dared ask who won."
"'I'm certain that the fate of Markov Manor is connected to these cryptoliths . . .' This Tamiyo was on to something."
"'I've seen hornworms big as a man's fist,' the traveler said, and nodded soberly when our jaws went slack at his ignorance."
"'Invincible' is just a word."
"'O miserable of happy! Is this the end Of this new glorious world . . . ?'"
"'O miserable of happy! Is this the end Of this new glorious world... ?'"
"'Ownership' is such a gray area."
"'That was a narrow escape!' said Alice, a good deal frightened at the sudden change, but very glad to find herself still in existence."
"'Tis a shame, in such a tempest, to have but one anchor."
"'Tis distance lends enchantment to the view, And robes the mountain in its azure hue."
"'Tis now the very witching time of night, When churchyards yawn and hell itself breathes out Contagion to this world."
"'Tis the set of sails, and not the gales, Which tell us the way to go."
"'Tis the set of sails, and not the gales, Which tells us the way to go."
"'Twas when the seas were roaring With hollow blasts of wind . . . ."
"'Utterly' is my favorite way to destroy something."
"'War is no picnic,' my father liked to say. But the Ants seemed to disagree."
"'We have no legs,' the warrior spat, 'for we have finished running.'"
". . . 'First take Jingzhou, next the Riverlands;  On that rich region, base your own royal stand.' . . ."
". . . Before honor is humility."
". . . But I'm not tired!"
". . . But the time of Han had run—could he Kongming not tell?—  That night his master star fell past the hills. . . ."
". . . By six offensives from the hills of Qi Kongming sought to change Han's destiny. . . ."
". . . Cao's abdication changed the face of all;  No mighty battles marked the Southland's fall. . . ."
". . . Dry-walkers die We feed on sweet flesh . . . ."
". . . It was Pang Tong's boat-connecting scheme That let Zhou Yu accomplish his great deed."
". . . Jiang Wei alone still strove with might and main:  Nine times more he fought the north—in vain. . . ."
". . . Near death in Baidi, having reigned three years,  Bei sadly placed his son in Kongming's care. . . ."
". . . Our castle's strength Will laugh a siege to scorn."
". . . The ghost rides forth to the scene of battle in nightly quest of his head . . . he sometimes passes along the Hollow, like a midnight blast . . ."
". . . The kingdoms three are now the stuff of dream,  For men to ponder, past all praise or blame."
". . . The world's affairs rush on, an endless stream;  A sky-told fate, infinite in reach, dooms all. . . ."
". . . Three kings no more—Chenliu, Guiming, Anle.  The fiefs and posts must now be filled anew. . . ."
". . . Zhong Hui and Deng Ai next led armies west:  And to the Cao, Han's hills and streams now passed. . . ."
". . . [A]nd gives to airy nothing A local habitation and a name."
". . . [S]creams of horror rend th' affrighted skies."
". . . and I will bring the fury of the wild back to my village."
". . . and embrace the ancient ferocity of the undying Wild."
". . . and for that I shall be eternally grateful."
". . . and the waters were a wall unto them on their right hand, and on their left."
". . . and when the farmer awoke the next morning, all the seeds from his field were once again in their sacks."
". . . because to be honest, I couldn't tell you."
". . . but until this morning, I'd never seen them be of one body."
". . . heck, I'd settle for anything that even resembled a werewolf."
". . . inviting the soul to wander for a spell in abysses of solitude . . . ."
". . . it's that the lure of the sea is impossible to ignore."
". . . pirates gambled with a djinn and lost the thing more dear than gold."
"... Is it over?"
"...There was no trace Of aught on that illumined face..."
"...There was no trace Of aught on that illumined face...."
"...and now they're trying to make a brick wall on my property fight a dinosaur to the death."
"487. You're welcome."
"A basilisk's gaze is effective, but disposing of physical remains is a tiresome task. It's far more discreet to dissolve one's victim entirely."
"A basilisk's gaze is effective, but disposing of physical remains is a tiresome task. It's far more discrete to dissolve one's victim entirely."
"A battle's outcome is never certain."
"A beauty made more so by its fleeting visitations."
"A better Ravnica begins with a better Simic."
"A blade is not fully forged until it is given."
"A blessing is not a gift. It is a duty."
"A bolt to the eye, a blade to the neck. That's the way to clear the deck!"
"A boon from the angels should never be cast aside."
"A brilliant light can either illuminate or blind. How will you know which until you open your eyes?"
"A burst of hot air tossed the moon into the air, and the moon liked it up there so much it never needed the ground again."
"A church is just wood and walls. A congregation is the faithful praising the angels."
"A company of infantry is trapped behind the lines. We need to strike hard and fast to free them, or the casualties will be horrific. Send the griffins."
"A creature's bloodscent is a beacon that cannot be disguised."
"A cyclops thinks slowly but strikes quickly. Try to keep it thinking."
"A dash of cool water does wonders to clear a cluttered battlefield."
"A debtor's soul has little value, except as a warning to others who might consider defaulting on their loans."
"A display of humility is required of those who still possess such frailties."
"A double-edged sword lets you cut down your enemies with the backswing as well."
"A failure is simply another opportunity for improvement. Just wait until you see what I come up with next."
"A few arrows aren't enough to pierce your faith, soldier. You'll be back on the battlefield by sun's dawn."
"A flash of the lightning, a break of the wave, He passes from life to his rest in the grave."
"A fool's fire is quickly quenched."
"A gargoyle's meat can be carved with an ordinary cleaver, but for its petrous hide . . ."
"A good Tarpan will serve you, faithful and true. A bad one will kick you in the head."
"A good day in Goldmeadow is one in which I don't spend all evening picking quills out of my backside."
"A good explorer has to be as slippery as a gomazoa, as tough as a scute bug, and luckier than a ten-fingered trapfinder."
"A good guard is alert. A great guard is also loyal."
"A good lagac will carry you through thick and thin. A bad one . . . well, it's a tasty dinner."
"A good lagac will carry you through thick and thin. A bad one … well, it's a tasty dinner."
"A good tarpan will serve you, faithful and true. A bad one will kick you in the head."
"A good whack on the head usually has the same effect."
"A great warrior studies many different disciplines and takes the best from each."
"A great wave crashed, and a mighty wind blew out the stars."
"A grudge is a tattoo worn on the inside."
"A hedron holds magic for a thousand years—or less, if need be."
"A herd is only as strong as its weakest. Our weakest just killed his third minotaur raider—today."
"A horrible sight, yes, but the sounds . . . Its twanging tendons and grinding gears are almost musical."
"A jigsaw puzzle that lives, breeds, and thinks."
"A keen eye and steady hand are essential for defeating most foes, including hunger."
"A keen mind wields an army as a deft hand wields a sword."
"A key weakness in the design is its vulnerability to repeated, forceful blows."
"A kick from its hooves is like a bolt of lightning. I'd know. I've been hit by both."
"A life is measured by the lives it saves."
"A little dark magic won't stop me. The worse the curse, the better the prize."
"A long and difficult incision revealed that all vital organs are housed in the head, save for a long chain of stomachs, forty in all, leading from its throat to the end of the tail."
"A mage must be precise as well as potent; cautious, as well as clever."
"A man, and such a fool! I, a woman, will fight them for you."
"A massacre? It is a mercy we grant them. This way they won't freeze to death."
"A master of hieromancy can see the advantage in any scenario."
"A might spell can be handy against baloths, giants, kraken, the Roil—or if you lose your bearings in the woods."
"A mind in agony is a sparrow without wings."
"A mind may be steeled against madness, but all battlements fall in time."
"A minion given over to Tevesh Szat is a stronger minion gained."
"A mysterious people indeed. Their origins are as secret as their traditions."
"A pangolin's power grows with its speed. Strike when you have the chance!"
"A perfect fusion of nature and artifice."
"A perfect reflection of its world: brutal, fetal, and lacking truth."
"A potion is no substitute for a skilled surgeon, but it will hold your bits in."
"A problem is only a problem if you don't have the tools to correct it."
"A quick step beyond oblivion lies a place so full of thoughts that it leaves no room for your own."
"A rare and fascinating phenomenon."
"A relic donation is suggested."
"A renegade rallying the rabble does not a true Crusader make."
"A resourceful mage has many sources of information. The best one is your foe."
"A responsible king walks among his subjects."
"A ribbon torn will ward away dark dreams."
"A richer people could give more but they could never give as much."
"A riddle is nothing more than a trap for small minds, baited with the promise of understanding."
"A rift opened, and our arrows were abruptly stilled. To move was to push the world. But the sliver's claw still twitched, red wounds appeared in Thed's chest, and ribbons of blood hung in the air."
"A river of lava is just another river to cross."
"A ruler wears a crown while the rest of us wear hats, but which would you rather have when it's raining?"
"A rumor passes among the snakes, whispered by the rushes, inspiring the seekers: the goddess Freyalise is alive in Skyshroud."
"A sacrifice made in peace is worth a dozen made in panic."
"A shrill creature that delights in the misery of others—what's not to love?"
"A simple trap in a dark corner of the mind, and their nightmares catch up with them."
"A single dedicated mind can bring about the greatest destruction. That, or goblins—goblins work too."
"A single drop of blood draws their attention, then they strip your bones clean before you have time to die."
"A single grain of sand is insignificant, but a sandstorm can reduce pyramids to dust. Stand with your crop. Become the storm."
"A single item acting as lantern and lance? Now that's military efficiency."
"A single tree does not a forest make. We are stronger when we stand together."
"A skilled decoy can throw your enemies off your trail. A master decoy can survive to do it again."
"A slayer gets by on wits and reflexes."
"A small price to keep such pretty things safe."
"A splendid talent, admired of all men! His folly lay in serving Cao Cao's power."
"A stunning example of the breed! Flawless plating, ruthlessly efficient death stroke, and an excellent drool shimmer."
"A system to direct the flow of Ravnica's entire water supply? Thinking a bit small, aren't we?"
"A tempest is coming. Turn your faces toward the wind!"
"A thankless job, and a death sentence besides."
"A thick fog obscures the port of Leor, but it's not thick enough to muffle the screams."
"A tiny flame is enough to dispel the night."
"A touch of lightning, and anyone can be taught to dance."
"A touch of vine sap in the blood, and the flesh knits as quickly as new roots twining."
"A trail of scrap metal can lead it into an ambush. But take care not to overfeed it."
"A treasure to guard other treasures is worth the highest price."
"A true Phyrexian predator. It will never know death, just as nature intended."
"A true warrior fights with whatever's handy."
"A vizier's dish, best served drenched in honey and almonds."
"A wanderer has told me of an assassin in the Takenuma Swamp who uses her dark arts to animate her enemies' shadows against them. A wild tale, but it explains much."
"A warrior without wit is simply meat."
"A well-made wrench is a versatile, indispensable tool."
"A well-trained force brings peace... which brings more time for training!"
"A werewolf's howl is terrifying, to be sure. But this . . . this was a chilling sound I somehow felt. I fear what will reply to it."
"A whole life, full of memories and experience, love and sorrow, drained drop by drop into this bottle. Could any feast be more glorious?"
"A whole skin is worth a thousand victories."
"A wisp of life remains in the undergloom of Death; a visible form, though no heart beats within it."
"A world without evil? Boring. Give me vile fiends to smite and banish any day."
"A zombie's bed must be a lumpy one or he wouldn't leave it so often."
"AIIIEEEE!"
"Abandon ship!"
"About the sphinx, I have mixed feelings. Their wisdom I crave, but their secrecy I can't tolerate."
"About, about in reel and rout The death-fires danced at night; The water, like a witch's oils, Burnt green, and blue and white."
"Above all, a well crafted Thrull should be hideous—blasted of countenance and twisted of limb—to inspire fear and revulsion."
"Above the waves you may be mighty indeed, but down here you belong to me."
"Above them all is Truth, and Truth must be set free. If the wings of Truth are clipped, the voices will fall silent."
"According to accepted theory, the Grenade held some kind of flammable mixture and was carried to its target by a hapless Goblin."
"Ach! Hans, run! It's the Lhurgoyf!"
"Ach! Hans, run! It's the lhurgoyf!"
"Across the land rebellions seethed and swarmed  As vicious war lords swooped down on all sides."
"Across the plains, farmers who braved the mists began to vanish. Most blamed the goblins; none guessed the truth."
"Across the rift of battle, a bridge of gossamer. And for one moment, it holds."
"Adopt the character of the twisting octopus, which takes on the appearance of the nearby rock. Now follow in this direction, now turn a different hue."
"Aether is the soul of Kaladesh, and all souls should be free."
"After Auntie brushed the soot from her eyes, she discovered something wonderful: the fire had turned the goat into something that smelled delicious."
"After General Takeno found the Oathkeeper amidst the bamboo marshes, more scavengers braved the swamp's nezumi, oni, and kami in hopes of glory."
"After Lacjsi's speech, the Knights grew determined to crush their ancient enemies clan by clan."
"After everything I've survived, it's hard to be frightened by anything anymore."
"After four thousand years, you learn to plan for betrayal."
"After his death, monks spent ten years transcribing the tattoos from Reki's body and gathering stories from those who spoke with him. Thus the volume you hold was written."
"After making me, Zhou Yu, did you have to make Kongming?"
"After the Rising, a treefolk's mind is as limber and green as its limbs, and is at its most receptive to our teachings."
"After the death of her mother, Cassia found that things that appear fragile can be very strong indeed."
"After the people flee, but before the enemy arrives—that's grabbin' time."
"After the storm, I found a sea turtle dying on the sands, a blade of grass driven through its shell."
"After waking to the magic of Llanowar, no dreams can compare."
"Afternoon, folks. Lovely day for a stroll with my authentic human baby."
"Ah, I remember my first death."
"Ah, a faceshredder. Very rare. Nearly unstoppable. Good luck"
"Ah, again it does not bode well for you."
"Ah, this is a nice life. I can see why you were so desperate to keep it."
"Ah, to be young again."
"Ahh! Opposable digits!"
"Air hot with sulfur.  Earth heaves beneath me.  Could it be the mountain  ate something bad?"
"Airships are too confining. If I'm in the sky, I want to feel the wind in my hair and taste the aether."
"Ajani goes where he is needed most and in his name we keep his lands safe."
"Aku, City of Hidden Graves  Aku, City of Lost Kings  Aku, welcome me."
"All Dauthi are jackals, regardless of breed."
"All I ask is complete obedience."
"All animals—even humans—can be herded. The trick is to make them think they choose their own destination."
"All are not equal—neither in life nor after death. Bontu's favorites will stand highest in eternity."
"All armies prefer high ground to low and sunny places to dark."
"All beings carry the fire inside them. The challenge is to unleash it before they dwindle into oblivion."
"All beings have an inner light. Let me show you yours."
"All bonds are parasitic. Only rulership is pure."
"All clouds should be so organized."
"All consciousness is one, separated only by a thin veil of the physical."
"All dead move to the hollow rhythm of necromancy."
"All ends in obliteration—love in hatred, life in death, and light in empty darkness."
"All glamers lifted, all lies revealed, all flesh exposed."
"All hail the Demonlord Belzenlok, Evincar of the Stronghold, Scion of Darkness, Doom of Fools, Lord of the Wastes, Master of the Ebon Hand, Eternal Patriarch of the Cabal . . ."
"All kami are our enemies now, A very tough lesson to learn. But it's one that's taken quickly, When you feel what it's like to burn"
"All knowledge has its price."
"All life is driven by an indomitable will to survive. I simply turn that into something more . . . tangible."
"All men have their appointed time; that's something no horse can change."
"All my life I've fought these monsters. Today I finish that fight."
"All my spells smell like burnt hair lately."
"All of Ravnica's looking for you, Dack, from the Wojek on down."
"All of those Consulate safety measures undone with one simple tweak."
"All plans begin as dreams. I intend to awaken them."
"All questions will be answered during the Hour of Revelation."
"All right, let's light 'em up"
"All rivers eventually run to the sea. My job is to sort out who goes first."
"All struggles ultimately require sacrifice. It's just that some sacrifices are dearer than others."
"All that concerns me is the vampires' sense of smell and those freezing Nephalian nights."
"All that matters is the path ahead."
"All the dead sleep lightly here, no matter how refined their beds may be."
"All the knowledge of Lat-Nam could not protect its sages from the Brothers' War."
"All the power you have gathered for yourself, Liliana, I can take away."
"All the sylvan secrets of this world are etched between my rings. The skinfolk's metal aberrations can rot between my roots."
"All the tortures of my vault of horrors pale in comparison to dealing with those petty Bureaucrats."
"All the wizardry in the world has to pass through one small and easily sealed door."
"All things must eat, after all. Even the air can hunger."
"All things return to their beginnings. The waters that spill across the Kamitaki Falls flow to sea, only to be returned to her as the rain that joins the mighty river."
"All this nonsense made by magesRusts and crumbles through the ages."
"All this time I thought Squee was useless,"
"All tinkerers have their heads in the clouds. I don't intend to stop there."
"All warfare is based on deception."
"All we could lose, we did. All we could keep, we do. And both are shrouded by mists."
"All we had left were their black and bloated bodies."
"All we know about the Krosan Forest we have learned from those few who made it out alive."
"All will be reforged in the fires of glory."
"All your steel won't protect you if your will is weak."
"Allow me a moment to catch your breath."
"Allow zealous flames to light your path and the glory you seek will be revealed."
"Although Icatia's Combat Medics borrowed much of their knowledge from other societies, their skills were their own."
"Although armor and auras can be similar, the brains required to use them are worlds apart."
"Although my official log will state there is no evidence pointing to the existence of the Mistfolk, my certainty is lessened by the cursed consistency of the expedition's eyewitness accounts."

"Although nowhere on Kamigawa was safe during the war, the Takenuma Swamp was the most horrifying. The rotting bamboo itself rebelled against its mortal inhabitants, pulling them into unmarked graves."
"Although the Dwarves staunchly defended their walled city-states against the Orcs, their civilization was the first to fall, and its name was sadly lost."
"Always a welcome sight breaking through the clouds."
"Always carry two spears."
"Always give your foes a choice when they have none."
"Amazing, isn't it, how scraps can come together to create such a wonder?"
"Amazing, isn't it, what humans will throw away when they're drowning?"
"Ambition requires clarity. If you have any doubts, they must be abandoned."
"An ancient court mage unified the houses into guilds to serve Zhalfir above their own interests. Even during the civil war, the guilds stood together, a testament to the wisdom of Teferi."
"An ancient, powerful force has overtaken the valley. I sympathize for its former inhabitants, but I rejoice for the land itself."
"An angel appeared in the smoldering skies above the fray, her clothes as flames, her armor as fire."
"An appropriately detailed model is indistinguishable from reality, and much easier to control."

"An army has filled the valley, but it's not like any army I've ever seen. There are no tents, no fires, no horses . . . just a sea of bodies, writhing and moaning, as if a pestilent village were sent to invade us."
"An entire order of mages who draw their power from Ravnica's smog? Yet another indicator of our world's decay."
"An idiot cannot hear sense, even when a thousand people speak it."
"An immense river of oblivion is sweeping us away into a nameless abyss."
"An imperfection in the perfect world? We can't allow that."
"An indrik's howl has destructive power much subtler than that of its crushing foot. The sound is mundane, but inaudible vibrations scatter and sunder magical contrivances."
"An innocent man died because of my anger. That knowledge will haunt me for all eternity."
"An unexpected ally."
"Ancient one, we have reached the promised shore. The Immortal Sun is near. Drink and awake."
"And Muzzio says my arguments have no teeth."
"And a horror of outer darkness after, And dust returneth to dust again."
"And all this time I thought we were tracking it."
"And darkness shall be cast from me For my soul resides in the Sun."
"And if you threaten me again, your shiny steel trousers will be sprouting daggerthorn vines."
"And that's when it was discovered that boggarts have just half a brain."
"And the flamingos said, 'Get out of our nest—we can't be seen with the likes of you!' So, the griffin ate them."
"And the ignorant shall fall to the squirrels."
"And the seraphs sob at vermin fangs In human gore imbued."
"And the unclean spirits went out, and entered the swine: and the herd ran violently . . . ."
"And the unclean spirits went out, and entered the swine; and the herd ran violently . . . ."
"And the unclean spirits went out, and entered the swine; and the herd ran violently . . ."
"And then I realized we all have skeletons on the inside. Why wait until the bodies are dead to control them?"
"And though she didn't get her honey, Auntie found something far more interesting."
"And through the drifts the snowy cliffs Did send a dismal sheen: Nor shapes of men nor beasts we ken— The ice was all between."
"And topples round the dreary west A looming bastion fringed with fire."
"And when this land is wasted, where will we go?"
"And who will stop me? You?"
"Angels and inquisitors terrorize villages, but no one seems to notice the stirring out at sea."
"Angels are simply extensions of truth upon the fabric of life—and there is far more dark than light."
"Angels? My feelings remain unchanged."
"Anger is fleeting; remorse is eternal."
"Another angry mob? When will they learn to leave me be?"
"Another day. Another avenging angel. Another clump of feathers to toss in the trash."
"Any day that I ride my horse up to my ankles in the remains of my enemies is a good day."
"Any dream is a robust harvest. Still, I prefer the timeworn dreams, heavy with import, that haunt the obsessive mind."
"Any fool can pick up a sword and charge into battle. To emerge alive at the end, that is a gift that comes from leadership and experience."
"Any fool who would die for honor is better off dead."
"Any good prospector must sift the gold from the sand."
"Any hotheaded cub can raise a sword in anger."
"Any oaf can conquer a kingdom. It takes true power to conquer time."
"Any scrap of compassion that still existed in my soul was permanently snuffed out when they cast me out into the flames."
"Any ship that sails on these mean seas for long is bound to pick up a ghost or two."
"Any who drink of Freyalise's bounty drink the mead of rebirth."
"Anybody want some . . . toast?"
"Anyone can snap her fingers and yank a soul. I prefer to kill creatively."
"Anything a falcon can do, a bat can do in pitch darkness."
"Anything we can do to hurt the Phyrexian invaders is worth dying for."
"Approach from behind. That way, if it does charge, at least you aren't in front of it."
"Archers, ballistae—you can't even get near the island of Avenant."
"Are the gods angry at our discontent with what they give us, or jealous that we made a thing they cannot?"
"Are you sure this is going to work?"
"Are you sure you want to do that?"
"Are you thinking what I'm thinking?"
"Aren't there boggarts enough in Lorwyn? Couldn't it turn into a sheep? Or a sunflower?"
"Argoth's doom rained from a clear sky. Yavimaya will not share that fate."
"Arise. You have been anointed by the light. Go forth and fight without fear, for you shall be victorious."
"Article 5.8.2. Ensure proper restraint of any and all arms, legs, claws, jaws, tails, tentacles, and tendrils as appropriate."
"Artifice has always stood upon nature's shoulders. Let us watch nature take a turn."
"Artifice sundered the world. It shall not again wreak such sorrow."
"As Argoth's last defenders fell to Urza's juggernauts, Titania said, 'Nature cannot be destroyed, only changed.'"
"As I desire, so it shall be."
"As I died, I rejoiced. I would see my family again. But then I woke up back on the battlefield. Back in Kamigawa. Back in hell."
"As Zendikar has bled, so will Innistrad. As I have wept, so will Sorin."
"As a child I saw something walking in the distance, far beyond the Hekma—shadow-dark, and taller than the gods. Even now, it passes through my dreams."
"As a child, I slept with a cloth over my face, to hide from the spirits that might pull the air from my lungs."
"As a great whale dies, it flips onto its back. And so an island is born."
"As a kid, I dreamed of flying on those wild drakes. They inspired me to build wings of my own."
"As equal were their souls, so equal was their fate."
"As far as I can tell, that frog dangling from the stick serves absolutely no purpose whatsoever."
"As flies to wanton boys, are we to the gods. They kill us for their sport."
"As if his chest had been a mortar, he burst his hot heart's shell upon it."
"As it charged our keep, I mistook it for a bear. After it tore through our ramparts and half the guard, I wished it had been a bear after all."

"As it moved, the wurm's spines gathered up bits of flowstone, which took the shapes of dead villagers' heads. Each head spoke a single sound, but if taken together, they said, 'Alas for the living.'"
"As long as I pull the strings, you will dance."
"As long as I stand, so will your cause."
"As long as Rushwood glows, no life is ever truly lost."
"As long as each side thinks it can win, the balance holds, and the mage-rings stand."
"As long as my faith persists, so shall I."
"As long as there is a single shred of life, there is hope"
"As long as there is a single shred of life, there is hope."
"As long as we can utter a prayer or lift a weapon, we have the power to fight back."
"As long as we have the will to fight, we are never without weapons."
"As long as we have walked this world, we have known it as a harsh and unforgiving place."
"As long as your courage remains, your life will not falter."
"As more oni walked Kamigawa, more darkness infested its inhabitants' souls."
"As much as I hate water, I do love fish . . . ."
"As my father taught, 'Training will raise your shield to the blow, but courage fills the gaps the shield leaves open.'"
"As my hands touched it, I realized that I had not found it—it had been leading me here."
"As my kha, he is the source of my inspiration. As my brother, he is the embodiment of my aspirations."
"As one, nature lifts its voice to tell you this: 'No.'"
"As our numbers dwindle, the ranks of the dead grow ever stronger."

"At the core of all power is raw passion."
"At this rate,"
"Atarka's people starve while she feasts upon the bounty of their hunts. They must conquer ever more lands just for the sake of their own subsistence."

"Attempts to revive this ancient species have not been entirely successful, but results indicate potential for future development."

"Avacyn emerged from the broken Helvault, but her freedom came at a price—him."

"Avoid anything that scuttles, scrabbles, or shambles."
"Aw, he's just a silly, dirty little man. What's to be afraid of?"
"Awake, and lift your faces to the sun."
"Awaken that which was never asleep."
"Aye, the foul beast chomped me, but I got away. You'd best believe when I find it again, it won't get away so easy."
"Bant is a world imprisoned by polished stone and tyrannical rule. It yearns to strike back against those who restrain it."
"Bant sentries were called the Angel Line. They never faltered, and they were ready to die defending their position."
"Bant's most gallant knights wear my sigil, and for that I am humbled."
"Baral took my family from me back then. I'd do anything to face him now."

"Barbarian raids were a concern to those living in the northwest provinces, but the Skyknights never dealt with the problem in a systematic way. They thought of the Balduvians as an 'amusing model' of their forebears' culture."

"Barbarian raids were a concern to those living in the northwest provinces, but the skyknights never dealt with the problem in a systematic way. They thought of the Balduvians as an 'amusing model' of their forebears' culture."
"Barbarian tribes with their rulers are inferior to Chinese states without them."
"Barbarians! They burned my favorite chair! We'll kill them all!"
"Barnacles are the sea's final defense."
"Barrin always said that reality is relative. 'The world,' he cautioned, 'is but pieces of one's perception.'"
"Barrin taught me that the hardest lessons to grasp are the ones you've already learned."
"Basically, we turn a bunch of little lightnings into one big lightning."
"Bathed in hallowed light, the infidels looked upon the impurities of their souls and despaired."
"Bats are welcome to eat thousands of my pets. I have multitudes more that will ultimately eat the bats."

"Be as fast as lightning, and you will be just as deadly."

"Be ever loyal to your own best interests."
"Be fearless, for a furious rebirth awaits you."
"Be like the grazers of the Saruli. Keep your herd close, and stay alert for encroaching danger."
"Be like the meerkat, my daughters: ever vigilant, true to your own, and wary of strangers."
"Be like the sea: flow around that which is unmovable; for everything else, crash into it unrelentingly."
"Be logical in all things. Do not allow instinct or passion to cloud your mind."
"Be silent and listen to your inner fire. Only then can you walk the Path of Flame."
"Be still."
"Be sure to get the tree in the picture."

"Being an inventor means knowing how to use the tools at hand to make something great—or to bring it down."

"Beware the merrows, whose envy and covetousness surpasses even that of the ravenous whirlpools where they dwell."
"Beware the seagrafs just off the shore. These waters are filled with hungry geists looking for an easy meal."
"Big one I, One big eye. One-eye see Two-eye die!"
"Big plants not only good for hidin', but full o' tasty bugs, too."
"Big, wicked, and not too smart. Poor thing never stood a chance against us, dear."
"Bind me to thee, my soul to thine. I am your servant and your slave. Blood for blood, flesh for flesh, Leshrac, my lord."
"Bind me to thee, my soul to thine. I am your servant and your slave. I shall hunger for your word and thirst for your blessing. Blood for blood, flesh for flesh, Leshrac, my lord."
"Birds know no borders! Why, then, should we?"
"Bitten? Save time, amputate now."
"Bitter water vicious wave Shadow-cold shallows root-made maze Home's angry embrace."
"Bitter water, vicious wave; Shadow-cold shallows, root-made maze. Home's angry embrace."
"Black spirits and white, red spirits and gray, Mingle, mingle, mingle, you that mingle may."
"Blades dull and armor dents. Marisi taught us that instinct is the only thing a true warrior needs."
"Blasted amateurs! Doesn't the queen think we can fight well enough on our own?"
"Blasted fishtails! It's not enough that they meddle with my head, but they twist my body as well."
"Blood drips. Blood sings. Blood devours all and only blood remains."
"Blood flows. Blood calls. Blood devours all and only blood remains."
"Blood from the vein is the finest vintage to accompany a feast of the mind."
"Blood is constant. Every drop I drink, someone must bleed."
"Blood is foul, the flesh dross. My ascendance thirsts for life itself."
"Bloodsuckers, howlers, monsters from the beyond . . . it doesn't much matter. I won't have to face them alone."
"Blow, fiery wind,  strip illusion from the eye.  Blow, fiery wind of truth."
"Blow, winds, and crack your cheeks! rage! blow!"
"Boasting impenetrable defenses only draws the most tenacious of attackers."
"Body and spirit are sworn enemies. They will take any excuse to be rid of each other."
"Boggart blood disgusts me almost as much as the foul creatures themselves."
"Bolas remade this place in his image. He has the advantage here. We must approach carefully."
"Booga booga booga!"
"Books can be replaced; a prize student cannot. Be patient."
"Boom Boom Boots the size of oxcarts, then an axe like a falling sun. Elves scattered. Trees scattered. Even the hills ran for the hills"
"Boom! Boom! Boots the size of oxcarts, then an axe like a falling sun. Elves scattered. Trees scattered. Even the hills ran for the hills!"
"Borborygmos's elemental launched an assault, but the Izzet wards held and experiments continue."
"Born and bred of fungus, Thallids were nearly impossible to kill."
"Born under the moon, the second child will stumble on temptation and seek power in the dark places of the heart."
"Born under the sun, the first child will seek the foundation of honor and be fortified by its righteousness."
"Boss told us to try and train 'em. Trained it to attack—it ate Flugg. Trained it to run fast—it got away. Success!"
"Bow before the might of—wait, what?"
"Bows and whips cannot save us from these new horrors of the Mephidross."
"Brackish water, dark and blind Heed my will, to you I bind."
"Braid her branches, life fulfilling Goddess loving, Goddess killing."
"Brassclaws were typical Orcs—quick to laud their own prowess in battle, quick to jeer at their opponents, and quicker still to run away when things started to look slightly dangerous."
"Brave scar or unfortunate tale? It all depends on your pain threshold."
"Bravery shines brightest in a pure soul."
"Break one in half and you'll get a decent—if gooey—pair of weapons."
"Break their formation! Thin their ranks! I'm right behind you!"
"Brilliant! They evolved away from energy-taxing brains and respond only to spinal reflex arcs from the hive mind."
"Bring down a stag and fix its horns upon Arel's head. She hears the wisdom of our ancestors."
"Bring down a stag and fix its horns upon her head. This one hears the whispers."
"Brute force can sometimes kick down a locked door, but knowledge is a skeleton key."
"Build a moat. If we're lucky, it can't swim."
"Burn it down, you say? Now there's a stupid idea. What do you suppose will become of those overhanging branches, hmm? And then what do you suppose will become of us?"
"Burn their homes. Salt their lands. Nothing survives."
"Burn. Burn. Keep. Burn"
"Bury your dead deep. The boars are hungriest while the corpse is still warm."
"But I signed nothing!"
"But high she shoots through air and light, Above all low delay, Where nothing earthly bounds her flight, Nor shadow dims her way."

"But why can't I get one?"
"But you said 'when goats fly!'"

"Buying old, worn-out junk. Selling marvels of real value."
"By Avacyn's decree, we shall cleanse these relics of their demonic past."
"By accepting my smallness I am vast."
"By all means, keep trying."

"By the time your knees have worn through your robe, you may have begun to learn your place."

"Call every able sword to our side. Kjeldor will stand triumphant!"

"Can't a fella get a moment's peace around here?"
"Canyons in the Phoberos badlands are essentially gates to the Underworld."
"Captain, I think that island is following us."

"Carrion! Keep your distance. My blade will come to you!"
"Carry war to the Dauthi, no matter the way, no matter the world."
"Cast out by my tribe, I am a pariah trapped in this mammal's carcass. Only my true kin hear my cries."
"Catch good today. Start replacing crew tomorrow."
"Catch me if you can."
"Catch!"
"Challenge me with your strongest. I will paint my sword with their blood."
"Chancellor Rayne canceled the annual beeble roast. I should have married a crueler woman."
"Change your mind, or I'll change it for you."
"Changes far greater than the turning of the leaves await us at season's end."
"Channel your vitality through me."
"Channeling the white-hot power of all five suns creates a pretty good diversion."
"Charge bravely. Fight selflessly. Act honorably. Iroas will watch over you."

"Choices belong to those with the luxuries of time and distance. We have neither. I recommend we proceed with the plan to destroy all shrines of the kami."

"Civilization is fertilizer."
"Civilization is the sum of Ephara's gifts."
"Civilization will subsume us unless we overwhelm it instead."
"Clerics give up when their patients die. Can I help it if I'm more compassionate?"
"Clever folk build their homes near cloudcrowns. If a hawk or even just a faerie tries to swoop in, it'll get swatted from here to Cloverdell."
"Close your ears to the voice of greed, and you can turn a gift for one into a gift for many."
"Combat is a form of worship, the clash of steel a solemn prayer."
"Come back, cowards! Everyone knows Merfolk can't wield magic!"
"Come in, yes? Is warm!"
"Come on, it's not even that deep!"
"Come on, you twisted things! Don't you want to get acquainted?"
"Come one, come all! this rock shall fly From its firm base as soon as I."
"Come, let me free you of the tyranny of thought."
"Come, little one. Unfurl your wings, fill your lungs, and release your first fiery breath."
"Come, my beautiful brothers and sisters. Let us hunt."
"Come, my wild children. Let's give the interlopers a woodland welcome."
"Come. Bring your brothers. Tonight, you feast on living flesh."
"Comes right outta th' ground. If ya can smell it, it's too late."
"Comfortable even in a furnace? I've never met one who'd accept my wager."
"Comin' through!"
"Coming down is the best part!"
"Command is the act of balancing on a vine and convincing others that it is firm ground."
"Commander, we caught the Dimir spy and took her ashes into custody."
"Common soldiers can't understand what a sidar knows: the enemy can be a resource."
"Compared to the hunger of the fires within the earth, the appetite of a mere wurm is nothing."
"Concentration is key. Without it, a mage conjures nothing but a splitting headache."
"Conquering your first world is the hardest, after all. My power grew as I moved from world to world, taking anything that would make the next taking easier."
"Consider my debt to your kin paid in full."
"Consider not what the mask hides, but what it can reveal."

"Contrary to popular wisdom, I find it's best to fight fire with its opposite."
"Control the Great Conduit? You might as well try to divert a river with your hands."

"Controlling time ensures you need never look impulsive again."
"Corpses for crew don't sit well with me. Zeki and his dead ship had best keep their distance."
"Cosi has many followers. Even the volcano finds a way to do his bidding."
"Could there be a fouler act? No doubt the Baron knows of one."
"Could there be a fouler act? No doubt the baron knows of one."
"Courage is a proud and gleaming shield. It does not bend or hide from sight. To fight with courage, we must forge in steel."
"Courage is the only shield I need."
"Course he ran! I wouldn't want to stare down that barrel, either!"
"Cowards die many times before their deaths; The valiant never taste of death but once."

"Crackle"

"Craghorns experience a wide range of emotions: rage, fury, anger . . ."

"Cry to the sun and watch as even your tears forsake you."

"Even from miles away, I could see our eagles circling. That's when I knew we were needed at home."

"Fly as an arrow through the trials, and never waver in your course."

"Folks 'round here are too in love with their contraptions. Does them some good if we smash every one so often."

"Four things that never meet do here unite To shed my blood and to ravage my heart, A radiant brow and tresses that beguile And rosy cheeks and a glittering smile."

"Freedom lies in accepting a single path."
"Freyalise has cleansed our bodies and minds of the plagues of Kjeldor; all she asks in return is that we keep pure our newly given home in Fyndhorn."
"Friend and foe alike are irresistibly drawn to its beauty—the good, to their lasting reward, and the evil, to their brief and painful regret."
"From a great bonfire at the dawn of time, the first Gruul kindled their rage. The same flame burns in you."
"From a sea of infinite possibilities, our choices create the future."
"From a tiny sprout, the greatest trees grow and flourish. May the seeds of your mind be equally fruitful."
"From down here we can make the whole wall collapse!"
"From here, let the world be reborn."
"From in here, everything looks like dinner."
"From the ashes of Reito rose a new kami. And thereafter at every battle came Horobi, Death's Wail."
"From the first touch, I know exactly what the metal wants to be."
"From the highest towers to the deepest sea, all life must be touched by etherium."
"From the mouths of my servants, my voice shall emerge to shake the souls of my foes."
"From the sea came all life, and to the sea it will return. The sooner the better."
"From the snowy slopes of Kaelor, To the canyons of Bandu, We drink and fight and feast and die As we were born to do."
"From the swallows, I learned how to ride the winds to anywhere, and from my tears, I mastered how to harness the water."
"From the volcanoes of Shiv to the Balduvian steppes, I have sought a worthy teacher. At last, I have found one."
"From up here we can drop rocks and arrows and more rocks!"
"From void evolved Phyrexia. Great Yawgmoth, Father of Machines, saw its perfection. Thus The Grand Evolution began."
"From void evolved Phyrexia. Great Yawgmoth, Father of Machines, saw its perfection. Thus the Grand Evolution began."
"From womb of nothingness sprang this place of beauty, purity, and hope realized."
"From your death, new life. From your loss, our profit."
"Full fathom five thy father lies; Of his bones are coral made; Those are pearls that were his eyes; Nothing of him that doth fade, But doth suffer a sea-change Into something rich and strange."
"Full of beauty and grace, with a predator's instincts. . . Although she wanders, I have always thought Mirri belongs in Llanowar most of all."
"Furballs? Try dealing with fireballs."
"Fyndhorn is our home."
"GOTCHA!"
"Gaea sings with the voice of nature rampant: a thousand howls, chitters, and cries, and none of them can be ignored."
"Gaea's memory is eternal, and she exists in all things."
"Gambling with mages never is."
"Garb is for common folk. I prefer to wear insight and zeal, ambition and flame."
"Garl, adjust the slurry dispensers. Garl, fetch more corpses. Garl, quit crying and give me your brain tissue. If he doesn't stop being so rude, I'm quitting."
"Gather round and tell me all from the courts and castles."
"Gazing at the unicorn, I felt closer to the majesty of Nyx than I ever had before."
"Geists wish to make themselves known. I'm merely the vessel for their efforts."
"General Takeno glared at us as if we were the enemy. 'The day is not over yet,' he shouted, 'and unless you have a nezumi's heart, you will stand and fight'"
"General?!"
"Geralf, must you always whine? I agreed to nothing. I'll raise ghouls anytime I wish."
"Get behind me!"
"Get it? Bunnies, letters, -X-X? Me neither."
"Get out of my way."
"Get ready, son."
"Get up, blast you! They're attacking! Why are you all so slow?"
"Get up, slugabeds! We've got company, and they're not dressed for a party!"
"Get up. You're not finished yet."
"Getting people to do what you want is merely a matter of telling them what they want to hear."
"Ghirapur's gremlin population poses a threat to the infrastructure of the fairgrounds. Threats must be eliminated."
"Ghoulcallers trying to get in, geists trying to get out . . . . This duty is never dull."
"Ghouls smashed the door, but I heard the call of the gryffs and knew we were saved."
"Gideon, how easy it must be to play the protector when you think yourself untouchable. How wrong you are."
"Give 'em a push."
"Give it a week and it will feed an army."
"Give me . . . some skin."
"Give me a bit of steel and I'll deliver it into the hearts of my enemies."
"Give me a crew like this one and I'd rule any sea I sailed."
"Give me a sturdy rope over the advice of any so-called expert. I can thread the dark wilds better than anyone."
"Give me a sword and I'll kill a few enemies. But give me a hammer and a fiery forge, and I'll turn the tide of battle."
"Give me a thousand such Warriors and I could change the world."
"Give me eight walkers, I'll give you the city."
"Give me enough refuse and mana and I will summon an ooze that can engulf all of Ravnica."
"Give me some room."
"Give me wings to fly and speed to strike. In return, the glory I earn shall be yours."
"Give me your hand and I will give you victory."
"Give me your memories, and you will have release from the suffering they bring you."
"Give them everything you've got . . . and some things you don't."
"Give them great meals of beef and iron and steel, they will eat like wolves and fight like devils."
"Give thy ration to thy mount, if the road be long. So sayeth the bey."
"Give up these unnatural weapons, these scrolls. Heart and mind and fist are enough."
"Give us breath. Give us life. Prepare us for the day we make."
"Gix doesn't want a people to rule but puppets to entertain his madness."
"Glok loved bets He'd sit in the bar all night an' laugh an' laugh. Hey—he still owes me."
"Glok loved storms! He'd sit an' watch an' laugh through the whole thing. I miss him."
"Glorifying the will is a mistake. It is simply one more force to be mastered."
"Glorious, to walk again across the savannah with my beloved."
"Glory was gone; Glory was everywhere."
"Gnawed to death. Bad way to go."
"Go ahead, build another. I'll burn that down as well."
"Go ahead. Take it. You'll be so very powerful . . . and what harm can it do?"
"Go down there and fish him out. Maybe his hide will fetch a price."
"Go find yourself a couple of friends, and bring me a blindfold. Then we might have a fair fight."
"Go forth and cause trouble, my little one!"
"Go swiftly, clever arrow, and teach The philosophy of stillness."
"Goblins are cheap, but be careful. It's a lot easier to steal from a corpse than a customer."
"Goblins bred underground, their numbers hidden from the enemy until it was too late."
"Goblins build with true zeal—and anything else within arm's reach."
"Goblins charge with a deafening war cry. The cry doesn't mean anything—it just drowns out the drums!"
"Goblins cry, soldiers fly. Stones fly, soldiers die!"
"Goblins won't betray their own kind for any price. They'll do it for a very specific price."
"Goddess, grant us light to banish the world's shadows."
"Gods do not sleep soundly in the earth's embrace."
"Gone today, here tomorrow."
"Good is not a 'thing.' You can neither touch nor own it. No, Good is a vision we all share and strive to make real."
"Good neighbors make good walls."
"Good night."
"Good ol' rock. Nothing beats rock."
"Good soldiers rely first upon their training, then upon their instincts."
"Grab an axe and defend the gate! Your despair is an extravagance we can ill afford."
"Graceful? Yes. Beautiful? Absolutely. Harmless? Definitely not."
"Grant me loft. Grant me light. Grant me the accuracy I need to kill all who threaten Bladehold."
"Granted, it's the pinnacle of utter destructiveness. So what would you call two of them?"
"Graveyards are sacrilege! A waste of perfectly good bones."
"Grease up a firecannon good and proper with dinosaur-liver oil, and it'll shoot just about anything."
"Great Yawgmoth moves across the seas of shard and bone and rust. We exalt him in life, in death, and in between."
"Great art can never be created without great suffering."
"Great books are meant to be read, then read again backwards or upside down!"
"Great chains shall free our warriors."
"Great losses often bring only a numb shock. To truly plunge a victim into misery, you must overwhelm him with many small sufferings."
"Greed, rage, and bloodlust all lead to death at the hands of those who keep their heads."

"Grief and rage and nightmares fade
Where hope and comfort make their stand."
"Grief is as useless as love."
"Griffins do not serve. They give freely to those they trust."
"Grow food in dirt? Save time—eat dirt."
"Guaranteed to leave your enemies sufficiently stabbed, bitten, cleaved, or exploded."
"Guard your thoughts. You never know who might wish to take them from you."
"Guard, fetch me a mallet."
"Guess where I'm gonna plant this!"
"Guilds be damned. We can fend for ourselves."
"Guilty."
"Gunner"
"Ha, banishment? Be merciful, say 'death,' For exile hath more terror in his look, Much more than death."
"Halana grew brambles to create a barricade around our camp, hoping that it would keep the wolves out. That was a mistake for which we almost paid dearly."
"Half of your studies will be learning the laws of magic. The other half will be bending them."
"Hallowed be this assemblage of various stuff!"
"Hallowed be this assortment of diverse things!"
"Hallowed be this collection of miscellaneous items!"
"Hallowed be this compilation of mixed objects!"
"Hallowed be this gathering of eclectic products!"
"Hallowed be this potpourri of sundry goods!"
"Hammer out your doubts as you forge your weapon. To slay a dragon, your resolve must be stronger than your steel."
"Hang on. I'm just tidying up."
"Hang out our banners on the outward walls;  The cry is still, 'They come'; our castle's strength  Will laugh a siege to scorn."
"Hanna would give up her own life before she'd abandon the Weatherlight."
"Harah swung his sword mightily, but still the air held him fast."
"Hard to starboard! Starb— Abandon ship! Abandon ship!"
"Harmony is no longer an option."
"Have you ever cornered a wounded vampire? That's a walk in the cathedral garden in comparison."
"Have you ever killed insects nibbling at your crops? I think that's what the Eldrazi believe they're doing to us."
"Have you seen your face? Trust me, this will be an improvement."
"Have you spent a winter high in the mountains, where the ice walks and speaks to the wind? It is not a place for those who have not learned respect."
"Having conviction is more important than being righteous."
"He Guan Yu covered the ground on a thousand-li horse;  With dragon blade he took each pass by force."
"He asked if I had work for him. No wasn't the right answer."
"He blows a gust across the cliff to vanish in a breath of wind."
"He can cause a lot of pain and do it with no fuss. That's all good, but I just wish he didn't do it to us"
"He can split a marshfly in two from halfway across the range."
"He cocooned himself alone in his workshop for months. When he finally emerged, all broad grins and excited chatter, I knew he'd found his answer."
"He displays a perverse charisma fueled by avarice. Highly dangerous. Recommend civil sanctions."
"He expects a reward, but the only piece of silver he'll get from me is my blade in his gut."
"He has been to the heart of the wood. Did you truly expect to wield power over him?"
"He has learned much in his long years. And unlike selfish humans, he's willing to share."
"He has returned. He who brought the dark ones. He who poisoned our paradise. How shall we greet him? With swift and certain death!"
"He hasn't returned to the Cloud Forest. But I can still sense his calming presence."
"He is ambitious. Tireless. And utterly ruthless. Ideal for the frontier."
"He is judge, jury, and executioner because he killed them all."
"He kept generations whole before the Kami War, and now he turns his century of wisdom to healing the latest casualties."
"He knows he has a short span of life, that the day will come when he must pass through the wall of oblivion . . ."
"He makes up his own laws, and that's dangerous to all who love peace and prosperity. Kill him on sight."
"He outran arrows. He outran even the archers' insults."
"He smiles with poisoned lips."
"He spoke with the tongue of Angels; we fought with the strength of lions."
"He steals power from treasure after treasure, and what does it do for the ouphe? Nothing."
"He told us not to worry, and he walked into the cavern. The swirling mass of Eldrazi parted to admit him, then closed in his wake."
"He's a living library. He remembers everything our band of explorers has seen, and we can use that to our advantage."
"He's a lot like me, that masterless little kami . . . unimpressed by grandeur and never at a loss for a trick."
"He's big an' dumb an' ready to fight. A lot like ol' Hornhead here."
"He's got more finesse than most goblins. He smashes windows with his fist rather than his forehead."
"Healing is a gift the divine ones have shared with us. It is a sacred trust."
"Healing is a matter of time, but it is sometimes also a matter of opportunity."
"Healing is more art than magic. Well, there is still quite a bit of magic."
"Hear me, nameless, and obey."
"Hear me, stone, root, branch: be the fist of this land. Turn back those who trample upon your domain."
"Hear only the Cabal's voice. See only the Cabal's way. Speak only the Cabal's word."
"Hear that? No? That's a cat warrior."
"Hear us, Overmother. Let the strong thrive under your gelatinous hand, and let the weak writhe under your serrated heel."
"Heart of Sokenzan, I call to you! Lend me your fire."
"Heed my words, traveler. Plagues, war, desolation . . . all mere hints of what is yet to come from Dominaria's vault of horrors."
"Heed the lessons of our time: the forms of water may move the land itself and hold captive the fires within."
"Heel."
"Heidar has forced the sun into hiding, but it has not forgotten us."
"Hello, kindling."
"Helping people is mostly a matter of teaching them to help themselves."
"Hence 'banishèd' is banished from the world,  And the world's exile is death."
"Her lips suck forth; see, where it flies!"
"Her mind is an incredible mix of emotion and power. Even if I could grasp it, I couldn't hold it for long."
"Her soldiers' hatred for the Goblins is tempered only by their need for what the Goblins alone hold: knowledge of their mountain home."
"Her voice is damnation, unyielding and certain."
"Her voice is disaster, painful and final."
"Her voice is insight, piercing and true."
"Her voice is justice, clear and relentless."
"Her voice is the wilderness, savage and pure."
"Her voice is wilderness, savage and pure."
"Her will shall banish the shadows. Her might shall punish the lawless. Her beauty shall restore the light."
"Here and gone like a fleeting breeze."
"Here are some bones for you to choke on, dear brother!"
"Here fell Ishi-Ishi, King of the Flaming Pebbles, Scourge of the Mountain Kami, Lover of Goats. May his shell never burn."
"Here in Fyndhorn, the goddess Freyalise is generous to her children."
"Here in Fyndhorn, where Freyalise's power is strongest, the forest has its own opinion."
"Here is a companion who will never falter, no matter how desperate the battle!"
"Here lies Gond, hero of Safehold Taldwen. May he ever guide our quest."
"Here on going is heck the what?"
"Here sprouted the first seedling of Argoth. Here the last tree will fall."
"Here we go again."
"Here you lie then, Ugin. The corpses of worlds will join you in the tomb."
"Here's how ya win. Don't let the other guy hit back first."
"Here, kitty kitty. Here, kitty kitty. Aaaaugh!"
"Here, there is only truth."
"Here—have a Mudhole."
"Heroism is more than a single act; it is hundreds of small decisions, made every day, in pursuit of a heroic cause."
"Hesitation breeds dissension. To be worthy of the next life, you must never look back."
"Hesitation is for the faithless. My belief lends me speed."
"Hey lads, the moon's rising. All the better to watch him beg for mercy."
"Hi! ni! ya! Behold the man of flint, that's me!  Four lightnings zigzag from me, strike and return."
"Hi! ni! ya! Behold the man of flint, that's me! Four lightnings zigzag from me, strike and return."
"Hi!ni!ya! Behold the man of flint, that's me!  Four lightnings zigzag from me, strike and return."
"High in the Karplusans, death is swift and razor-clawed."
"High on a throne of royal state . . . insatiate to pursue vain war with heav'n."
"His companions are wise to follow him, for his foes dare not stand in his way."
"His mind is feeble. Feed him to the bats."
"His sacrifice shall not be forgotten. Now toss his body over there with the others."
"His strengths are pride, devotion, and ambition. His weaknesses are the same."
"His tenement is filled with the most vile, disgusting vermin. It's infested with rats, too."
"His tongue must be honey, the way he gathers ants to fight with him."
"History is a potent weapon."
"Hit where it hurts, and always hit first."
"Hmm . . . It looks kinda like a bug. Let's crack it open an' see if it tastes like one!"
"Hmm . . . maybe lotuses this year."
"Hold fast the line! Either we stop them here or we wake up in their guts!"
"Hold the line, for family and the fallen!"
"Hold the line, hold the li—"
"Hold tight. I've got a surprise for them."
"Hold up your spears. And try not to look like food."
"Hold your fire, obviously."
"Hold your position! Leave doubt for the dying!"
"Holy couriers guide aven spirits up to the home of the Ancestor."
"Holy places are no longer sanctuary from death, and death is no longer sanctuary from anything."
"Homarids spread northward from Sarpadia as the climate cooled, raiding coastal settlements for supplies."
"Home is where you can find a decent graveyard and strangers can disappear without awkward questions."
"Hone the knife and mourn the least. Three chimes to sound the sweet, grim feast."
"Honor rides before us. All we have to do is catch up."
"Honor this place, for our children's children will stand here and speak these same words again."
"Honor those who honor Fyndhorn above themselves."
"Honor your steed and it will carry you to great deeds—and bring you home to tell of them."
"Honor, guide my step."
"Honorable in battle, generous in death."
"Hop away now, little Eternal. Go eat some flies."
"Hope shall be the blade that severs our bonds."
"Horse and rider are often of one mind."
"Horse? Who needs a horse?"
"How blessed are some people, whose lives have no fears, no dreads, to whom sleep is a blessing that comes nightly, and brings nothing but sweet dreams."
"How can any Human hope to match our skills? We are children of Fyndhorn, and its sap runs in our veins."
"How can anyone fight so much yet enjoy it so little?"
"How can there be doubt in the presence of such blessings?"
"How can we hope to match the speed of lightning? The fury of storms? The power of mountains? The answer is simple. We cannot. I advise against this war."
"How can we outrun the sky?"
"How can we wage war against ourselves? What happens when the kami of our very souls rise against us? I answer simply: We cannot. We die. There can be no victory in this war."
"How can werewolves be considered abominations next to such creatures?"
"How can you claim the gods are merciless when they robbed the snake of its limbs to give the other creatures a sporting chance?"
"How can you serve me? By dying."
"How could I catch her when the trees conspired to stop me?"
"How could someone so small cause so much trouble?"
"How could you not hear it approach? It's a hippo!"
"How cute. Does it do any other tricks?"
"How do I know where aid is needed? Look around you."
"How do the vinebred feel? Fah! We do not ask the puppet how it feels when the puppeteer bids it dance."
"How do you stop a raptor from charging? No, seriously! Help!"
"How dull it is to pause, to make an end, To rust unburnished, not to shine in use, As though to breathe were life!"
"How easily your flames are quenched."
"How fascinating it is to watch the machinations of one's own mind play themselves out."
"How have I angered nature that she would imprison me in a labyrinth of grass?"
"How many more will die before you accept your fate?"
"How many people can you save in that thing?"
"How smooth his face, how sure his thoughts. I look forward to breaking his mighty will."
"How terrible to wander wishing only to escape oneself."
"How thin is the veneer of civilization! A modest measure of panic will wash it off completely."
"How thoughtful of the Legion to train its soldiers to fit our spell's specifications."
"How to punish the guilty is up to the Ancestor. Deciding who merits such punishment is up to me."
"How truly vast this city must be, that I have traveled so far and seen so much, yet never once found the place where the buildings fail."
"Hrrngh! Someday I'm going to hurl this . . . er . . . roll this . . . hrrngh . . . nudge this boulder right down a cliff."
"Huge walls of ice block further travel. We can't believe they are natural."
"Human enlightenment is a firefly that sparks in the night. Dragon enlightenment is a beacon that disperses all darkness."
"Human tenderness is simply weakness in a pretty package."
"Humanity has always envied the power of flight. So we took it."
"Humans are so forgetful. Every page I steal becomes a secret they can't remember."
"Humbly I bow. Silently I wait. Deeply I listen."
"Hunters feed on the fear of their prey."
"I abandoned my dream of a squadron of griffin-riders when the cost proved too high. Three trainers were eaten for every griffin broken to the bridle."
"I admire their courage as much as I despise their savagery."
"I admit, I am a creature of the city. The sights, the nightly excitement, the abundance of fine drink . . ."
"I almost envy them. They can't get frostbite."
"I alone determine my destiny."
"I always attack from where their spyglasses can't see."
"I always charge a little extra to take on a pegasus. They fly like eagles, kick like mules, and hide like hermits."
"I always thought the great insects of Tazeem were frightening until I saw the Eldrazi. Now I welcome the sight of mantises perched in the treetops."
"I am a dragonslayer for Lord Silumgar. There is no dragon save him whom I fear."
"I am an artist, a builder, a creator . . . I create the biggest explosions around."
"I am an instrument of the church wielded against Avacyn's enemies."
"I am as the wind that bears me: harsh yet gentle, fleeting yet ever-present. Together we fly beyond imagination."
"I am bound to all my children. I share in their joys, I rage at their injuries."
"I am but a humble traveler. I have no taste for sneakery nor thiefiness."
"I am condemned without end."
"I am confident that all our enterprises can benefit from this little revolution."
"I am confined by sleep and defined by nightmare."
"I am in my element: the element of surprise."
"I am irrelevant. The future I hold in my hands is everything."
"I am most myself when I am least human."
"I am my life's work."
"I am neither their drover nor their leader. To these majestic beasts, I am simply their herdmate and nothing more."
"I am no mere ship's captain. The north wind is my accomplice. The tide is my first mate."
"I am not Raksha. I never will be. But I refuse to be the kha who watched her pride be torn asunder."
"I am not afraid to die today nor afraid of what death will bring."
"I am older than any Elder Druid before me, and still no child has been born with the Mark to take my place. When will the wheel turn?"
"I am rooted in the life of all that thrives around me. You cannot move me."
"I am sewer-king!"
"I am that merry wanderer of the night."
"I am the banisher, the ill will that snuffs the final candle."
"I am the feeder, the morsel that revives the starving."
"I am the ferocity of the Burning Sun. I am hide and feather, fang and claw."
"I am the holy wind that shall avenge the Cabal's victims."
"I am the purifier, the light that clears all shadows."
"I am the rock of the polis. Death only strengthens me."
"I am the romancer, the passion that consumes the flesh."
"I am the simplifier, the root that drags all artifice to earth."
"I am the storm."
"I am the unraveler, the loosened thread that will not hold."
"I am the very soul of battle, but even I would never advise open war with the Conclave."
"I am weak. Make . . . me . . . ideal."
"I am who I pretend to be."
"I appreciate the depravity of noble designs turned to devious ends."
"I appreciate things that exceed expectations."
"I asked if they wanted to do things the easy way. I meant easy for me."
"I asked one of my aides how they do it, but all he'd say was, 'Trust me, Mayor, you don't want to know.'"
"I await your donation."
"I believe it when they say they're connected to the land—looks like somebody plowed her face."
"I believe many worlds will bow to Phyrexia. Mirrodin is merely the first."
"I bless the living with a song of death."
"I breathed deeply, and suddenly I knew not who or where I was."
"I bring a dawn that no night can follow."
"I bring a death none can escape."
"I bring a fire to recast all the world."
"I bring a flood that nothing can withstand."
"I bring a wilderness no law can tame."
"I bring baubles of lore, lost secrets seined from the listening waves."
"I bring word from Gaea. Fight on She will never allow her children to die alone."
"I call upon the vigor of the grasses, the hopes of the flowers, and the dreams of the trees."
"I can ail what cures you."
"I can call an army to my side in the blink of an eye. Best not blink."
"I can feel the strength of the entire forest."
"I can give you strength, but you'll have to bring your own courage."
"I can hear the plunder calling. It asks for me by name."
"I can hear the shamans chanting in the hills. They say their magic will protect us from the kami, that our gold has bought our safety. But no one sleeps soundly tonight."
"I can make you dance to my tune like a puppet, your very blood eager to obey."
"I can no longer sit in my workshop and ignore the events outside. My hammers strike for the people of Ghirapur."
"I can no longer stand by as these Skirsdag infiltrators rot the church from within. Even the Lunarch Council is compromised. What a fool I've been."
"I can post only the most honorable and strong-willed samurai to defend your stronghold. I have seen what can happen to lesser men."
"I can see which way the wind is blowing."
"I can see why this appeals to Thassa."
"I can staunch their blood, mend their flesh, and knit their bones. But I cannot restore their hope."
"I can tell you what you wish to know. But first, there is the matter of my fee."
"I can think of no greater punishment than answering your question in full."
"I can think of worse ways to go. On second thought, maybe not."
"I can't bear to see another plane broken before I make my own home whole. I'm sorry, but my watch is over."
"I can't believe they expect me to fight with this rabble. A Goblin in a big mask sends 'em running for cover."
"I can't claim to hunt all creatures. There are some things in the jungle that simply can't be hunted."
"I can't control its mind—I'm not even sure it has one. But I can dominate its will."
"I can't hear them scream, but at least I don't have to listen to them beg."
"I can't imagine how anyone lives in Shiv, let alone why they choose to stay."
"I can't think with all that screaming."
"I cannot teach you their brand of magic, but I can teach you how to defend against it."
"I care nothing for treasure. The land beckons me, and I cannot rest until my feet have touched every inch of it."
"I carry the light of truth. Do not pity those it blinds, for they never had eyes to see."
"I claim this land in the name of the queen."
"I come looking for demons and I find a plane full of angels. I hate angels."
"I concede it was a cheap shot, but it was the only one I could afford."
"I confer with Death itself. What could you possibly do to injure me?"
"I could demonstrate how the leonin sunsplicer works, but then you'd be too dead to buy one."
"I could heal a snakebite. Looks like you got bitten by a constellation."
"I could see in the other mage's eyes that he'd thought of it too. Then it became a race to exploit the knowledge first."
"I cover the land with blankets and it sleeps."
"I cradle my rage even as the earth cradles my dead kin."
"I crept up on him, quiet as a guttermouse. And then suddenly I found myself facedown in a latrine pit behind Tin Street Market."
"I cultivated my faith in Avacyn despite meager returns. Now my faith is repaid."
"I dance the nothing dance,  Feet in the air, knives in the ground."
"I deal so often in rotting corpses that when I come across the freshly dead . . . why, it's like my birthday come early."
"I decide what stands in my way."
"I dedicate my body to my country And my life to my King."

"Lord Silumgar has given you a second chance to please him."
