"Lost in the woods"
"Lost man, dead man, knocking on the door. Cankerman, soreman, knock no more."
"Loyalty guides me. Pride compels me. Anger sustains me. And the pay isn't bad."
"Loyalty to coin alone is loyalty nonetheless."
"Lucy, you've got some spleenin' to do."
"Ma said we should offer up blini-cakes and salt to the good ones, but I get that chill up my spine and just shut the door."
"Madness and genius are separated only by degrees of success."
"Madness can't touch a mind ignited by genius."
"Magic cast through a hand of flesh is just as weak as the flesh itself."
"Magic is like the tide—both ebb, both flow, and both serve my whims."
"Magic is my thread, my will the needle. I weave over you as if you never were."
"Magic overused can freeze the mind. Creativity is more important than power."
"Magic's only part of it, my friend. Diet does the rest."
"Make me thy lyre, even as the forest is: What if my leaves are falling like its own!"
"Make people wait for what they want, and you have power over them. This is as true for merchants and militia as it is for cooks and couples."
"Make sure he's pointed in the right direction before you light him. And don't let the goblins anywhere near the torch."
"Make sure those wretches feed only upon the plagued. The blood of the healthy is reserved for me alone."
"Make way! It's time for the final act!"
"Making a living in Kessig is hard, but I've learned some tricks of the trade."
"Mama says it's my imagination, but I know you'd never lie to me."
"Mammoths may be good to ride on, but they're certainly bad to fall off of!"
"Mana grows and changes like the roots of a plant. Like a plant, it must be nurtured."
"Mana lurks in all things, even in the depths of one's own heart."
"Mangara is gone. Who among you doubts that I have taken his power?"
"Manners are for mortals."
"Many Initiates sacrificed a hand to become full members of the Order."
"Many are in high place, and of renown: but mysteries are revealed unto the meek."
"Many believe it to be the manifestation of all that is vile about the boggarts. I believe it should be avoided—from upwind, if possible."
"Many great warriors died in the first days of the war, as the spirits of their weaponry turned against them with terrifying rage."
"Many have been lost to pity."
"Many have sought snake-twined Pharika's panacea. Do you wish to share their fate?"
"Many have walked here, but there is only one trail I seek."
"Many must die for the one who should not have perished."
"Many scales make the skin of a dragon."
"Many voices are needed to quiet this land."
"Many wearing rapiers are afraid of goose-quills."
"Many wings haunt the skies these days. Few of them bear good tidings."
"Marchesa's poison is delivered by more than daggers."
"Margaret has traveled with me to the end of the world and back."
"Marit Lage lies frozen in a glacier's heart. Still her dreams take form in our world, stealing the heat from our souls."
"Martyrs are cheaper than mercenaries, and a far better investment."
"Master your mind, or I shall master it for you."
"Mat'Selesnya sings out, and life flourishes in answer."
"May Svyelun and her tides favor you."
"May all the cairns of Jund be toppled."
"May angels fly at your back. May your blade cleave the darkness."
"May our blessings sever the tongues of the forsaken."
"May our foes choke upon its horns!"
"May starving fleas birth a thousand generations on your stubborn hide, cow!"
"May the Ancestor strengthen my hand and guide my blade."
"May the River claim Cho-Manno's body, wherever it lies."
"May the bounty of Kjeld enrich your days."
"May the forces that took Argoth beneath the waves never come among us again."
"May the light shine through me to guide the lost."
"May the memory of our fallen heroes ensnare the violent hearts of lesser men."
"May the skies be clear of gales and gulls."
"May the steel of your blade match the steel in your soul."
"May the winds blow till they have wakened death. . . ."
"May the worthy spend an eternity in Blessed Sleep. May the wicked find the peace of oblivion."
"May these deaths be the first of many."
"May they speed to their task, for the Skyknights alone cannot hold Kjeldor safe."
"May this blade guide you on your great journey, as it did me on mine."
"May you and all your kin waste and wither until your clan is no more!"
"May you be a stalker's dream."
"May you be strong and valiant, to defeat the enemies of the pure."
"May you decrease like coal upon the hearth . . . Evaporate like water in a pail, Become as little as a linseed-grain . . . And so diminish that you come to nothing."
"May you drink until you drown but never be sated."
"May you get the mount you deserve."
"May you rise again, from seed to sapling to sentience."
"May you shade three generations of seedlings."
"May you wake to find you were only ever a dream."
"May your day never match your expectations."
"May your horns get lodged in an Eldrazi's bony face, ornery brute!"
"May your veins weep, and may every vampire take notice."
"Maybe next time."
"Maybe they wanted to be on the winning side for once."
"Maybe we can trap them with bait,"
"Me? No, I'm not going to kill you. I won't even lay a finger on you. I promise."
"Meat *and* eggs. We eat!"
"Meat and eggs. We eat!"
"Melt that which was never frozen."
"Memnarch or the vedalken salvage most of the large machines, leaving us only scraps. Scraps are enough."
"Memnarch shall rage against us. We shall endure."
"Memories can't simply be washed away. The mind must be scrubbed clean."
"Men and rats both hunger: we for our playthings; they, for us."
"Mercadia's masks can no longer hide the truth. Our day has come at last."
"Merchants and politicians differ only in name."
"Merciless to the point of psychosis. Let's give him a job."
"Mercy? Mercy is for the playground, not the battleground."
"Metamorphosis is a process."
"Might doesn't just build empires. It protects them."
"Might of ancient wood and stone, Into spirit, flesh, and bone."
"Mind if I just lie down right here for a few weeks?"
"Mindlessness is not weakness. When we are lost to hunger we are unstoppable."
"Mine is an insatiable god, with appetites as magnificent as the jungle itself."
"Mine is not the warmth of compassion."
"Mine."
"Mists are carefree. They drift where they will, unencumbered by rocks and river beds."
"Mix the mortar with holy wards, or blood will run in the streets."
"Mizzium may be impervious to fire, but obviously certain other things can . . . modify its form."
"Modern Sarpadia's swarming with thrulls. It's a testament to the orcs that they've survived there so long."
"Mold could catch you."
"Molten earth has no anger of its own. Only by infusing it with your own rage can the magma seethe and take shape."
"Momentum is a great ally."
"Monsters dwell in every heart. We only think civilization tames them."
"Monsters will no longer find safety under the mists of Morkrut!"
"Moonlight has a way of showing all things as they truly are—for better or for worse."
"Moonlight offers sublime warmth that brings me a comfort sunlight cannot provide."
"Morality is just shorthand for the constraints of being powerless."
"More armies have been lost in the confusion of the jungle mists than to any battle."
"More children taken. This is an evil we will track without mercy."
"More of that strange oil . . . It's probably nothing."
"More rope may not be necessary."
"More than lessons may be gained from the past."
"More than snow falls from the Boreal skies."
"Mortal strength, like mortal hope, is so easily crushed."
"Mortals practice swordplay for a few decades at best. How can they ever attain the exquisite mastery that eternity has to offer?"
"Most compete for insects at street level. Some dwell near Izzet laboratories and ride the thermal updrafts."
"Most faeries are harmless pranksters. Every now and again, though, you get one that crosses over from mischievous to malicious."
"Most insects have been drawn to the Mirari. But all that remain in Wirewood are under my care."
"Most people believe magic is only a trick. Why change their minds?"
"Most people can't build decent weapons out of stone or steel. Trust the elves to do it with only mud and vines."
"Most wizards consider a thunderbolt to be a proper retort."
"Mowu was wary that day, as though he sensed the danger ahead."
"Much can be gained from the appearance of vulnerability."
"Much can be learned from the bees about dying for a cause."
"Murasan hurdas were too aggressive to tolerate a harness, so we put them on guard duty. Now the bandits can't get within spitting distance of us."

"Murder clad in crimson beauty,
An end to life and love and duty."
"Murder of the living is tragic, but murder of the idea is unforgivable."
"Muscle does not make one strong. It only masks the soul's light. True strength lies in purity of purpose."
"Mushroom Queen sits among her spores, Enjoying life and avoiding chores."
"Must not all things at the last be swallowed up in death?"
"My 'condition' is a trial. The weak are consumed by it. The strong transcend it."
"My Aesthir is my most trusted ally. We fight as one and live as one, and we will die as one."
"My Pete Venters theme deck is nearly complete. Then I shall be unstoppable! Bwahahahaaa!"
"My adopted children are loved no less."
"My ancestor Toshiro used to say, 'Life is a series of choices between bad and worse.' I'm a master of making great bad choices."
"My army took centuries to gather,"
"My arrows will ever find you."
"My battle cry reaches ears far keener than yours."
"My bowstring hums in tune with the song of the Worldsoul."
"My brain hurts."
"My brother and I both come from Balthor's forge. Kamahl has a temper of fire. I have a temper of steel."
"My brother, it may now be time to ring the bell and put out the call for aid."
"My cause is power, and at the altar of power I will gladly forfeit my soul."
"My cause is simple: To stop you, at any cost, from ever seeing the inside of this keep."
"My commands shall echo forever in their dusty skulls."
"My conquistadors are never slain, merely laid to rest."
"My course is before me. There is nothing behind me."
"My creations still can't match the dive speed of those floppy-winged mammals. Maybe I should enter one of them in the Fair."
"My criticism of the Izzet is that their impulse for learning seems too much like impulse and too little like learning."
"My destiny is to save others so their destinies may be achieved."
"My doors are called trespassing, my signatures, forgeries. They don't respect my talents, and I don't respect their labels."
"My dragonlord is immortal. Most dragons are not."
"My dragonlord's lightning will dance upon your bones!"
"My dreams darkened and seeped into my waking hours. Spellcraft and nightmare merged to create this monstrosity."
"My drivers are trustworthy. I removed their tongues myself. Any other questions?"
"My earliest work escapes me."
"My ears say it hisses. My fingers say it burns."
"My enemies will forget everything but their anguish."
"My enemies' death yields threefold benefit: removal, reuse, and research."
"My enemy's hatred is his weakness. My enemy's anger is my strength."
"My eyes are my strongest feature."
"My faith is stronger than fang, claw, or mindless hunger."
"My family protects all families."
"My family sheltered in her light, the dark was content to wait."
"My family was saved thanks to a single Boros soldier. It's why I joined the Legion. I will be the protector now."
"My favorite curses are those that manifest slowly, blackening the soul in ways the victim cannot hope to understand."
"My favorite guilty pleasure? Are there innocent ones?"
"My favorite part of getting into the infantry was getting out again."
"My finest creations are fashioned after the moths of Eiganjo. They fly higher, faster, and more gracefully than any of my own designs."
"My finest warrior was lost to the Phyrexians. I pray that Lady Selenia died honorably."
"My flesh holds no secrets, monster. The spirit of Mirrodin will fight on."
"My flock flew from a distant continent ruined by cataclysm and war. Benalia gave us shelter to end our exodus."
"My goat was a small price to pay for the chance to see the hunting griffin dive and seize it."
"My grandfather knew enough spells to fill a hundred scrolls. Nowadays, if a spell cannot fight the levelers, it is not even taught to our young."
"My grandmother had sold the rest of her jewelry long ago, but she left a particular necklace in my care: a golden chain, bearing a raven-shaped charm."
"My grandmother once told me the future of our world was inside the Weatherseed. When I touched it, I knew she was right."
"My greatest creation—me!"
"My greatest hope is that you will surpass me in every way, consigning my name to some forgotten corner of history."
"My heart and Zendikar's beat as one. Together we will endure."
"My heart filled with warmth, and I felt my feet lift from the ground. Suddenly, I was free—free to soar, the homes beneath me shrinking to specks on a map."
"My heart is not mine, it is Belzenlok's. All hearts are his, and all blood."
"My horizon was the arcing petals, my new home resplendent with spires of weeds and pillows of fragrant pollen."
"My lance was once wielded by Venerable Tarrian. In his name and by his might, I cast you down!"
"My left has felled a cyclops. My right has slain a giant. I bring both to every fight."
"My liege will lead and I will follow—to the battlefield, to the grave, and beyond."
"My life is yours, my lord. There is no greater service than to yield it for your safety."
"My lord, there is only so much I can do. This plague infests Krov worse than any other city."
"My mind and spirit are one—a barrier not readily passed."
"My mind has changed. My strength has not."
"My mind is the spread of the canopy. My heart is the embrace of the roots. I am deathless Llanowar, its fury and its peace."
"My mother once told me angels sing their swords' names with each strike."
"My motive is not vengeance but mercy. I deliver the soulless back to their severed souls."
"My mount needs neither reins nor bridle. We both share a common purpose."
"My new design has lightweight plating specially cultivated from heretics' spare tissues."
"My next aerial design will use less metal."
"My one regret is that I have mastered an art that leaves its audience unable to applaud."
"My only dream is to destroy the nightmares of others."
"My past holds only pain and loss. I will conquer it by creating the perfect future."
"My people are bound by masters centuries dead. Each artifact we destroy is another link broken in that chain."
"My people blazed these pathways long ago, before the Eldrazi came. We will ride them long after the Eldrazi are gone."
"My people serve the dragon Kolaghan, but I give my blood for a greater lord."
"My people swore to protect Benalia to the end. It is battered, but yet stands, as do we."
"My pet will pick the ripe fruit from your tortured brain as if it were hanging from a vine."
"My plan's elegance leads my enemies to believe it is spite that fuels me."
"My power is generosity, in a way. I give my survivors an appreciation for their lives."
"My predecessors taught me of duty and commitment. It seems they have more to teach."
"My priests swore loyalty to the Cabal not until death, but beyond it."
"My quest? Why, to marry Ayara. Or die trying."
"My scars are my sigils. I will wear them with pride long after you're gone."
"My secret ingredient? Well, I can't tell you that. But here's a hint. It's not love."
"My shield will bear a shining sun so you will always be with me.  Inlaid with gold, it will shine like glowing embers."
"My ship . . . ,"
"My shout is thunder and my fist is lightning!"
"My skill sharpens with each beat of my wings."
"My skills are wasted here."
"My soldiers fought without hesitation, died without doubt."
"My sorrow: to dream of simple times, and wake in mine . . . ."
"My soul thirsts for Serra's salvation, as does my body for life's breath."
"My specialty is theoretical universal limits and ways to circumvent them."
"My stride will break only against the twin points of Hazoret's spear."

"My success at navigating the Dark Meanders irritates the Inkfathom school. They consider themselves peerless divers, but I try to remind them that they cannot own commodities like bravery and cunning."
"My summoning begins your debt, Planeswalker."
"My summoning begins your debt, planeswalker."
"My sword is at your service, as are my scissors, corkscrew, and bottle opener."
"My tales of war are the stories most asked for around the fires at night, but they're the ones I care least to tell."
"My time will come, when all of the world will be reforged in the fires of my invention."
"My time will come, when every soul will bask in my glory and obey my law."
"My time will come, when life's frantic striving will fade into the boundless quiet of death."
"My time will come, when no road will divide the endless verdure of the trees."
"My time will come, when the rising tide will surge above the tallest mountain."
"My vengeance will drown my enemies as my storms drown the desert."
"My village's fear drove me into the wild . . ."
"My visions don't show me home. They show me where home is yet to be found."
"My whisper becomes a thousand roars."
"My work here is complete. The people have done everything required of them."
"My world is corrupted beyond cleansing. I must prevent this from happening to others."
"Mystic shadow, bending near me,  Who art thou?  Whence come ye?"
"Naga shed their scales. We wear ours with pride."
"Nature can't be stopped. It rips and tears at Ravnica's tallest buildings to claim its place in the sun."
"Nature cares not for the knowledge to be gained from its study. Better to bleed it dry, lest its potential be wasted on lizards and leaves."
"Nature does not need adornment."
"Nature has grown tired of the impositions of men and will begin to outfit its creations with tools for bloody instruction."
"Nature is a mutable cloud which is always and never the same."
"Nature is not always gentle or kind, but all life begets life."
"Nature is the endless dance between life and death."
"Nature's been fired. The oceans are under new management."
"Nature's exceptions remind us not to think in absolutes. Just as the orchid blossoms on blackened stone, so does the gift of mana occasionally manifest in the undead."
"Nature? Fire? Bah! Both are chaotic and difficult to control. Ice is structured, latticed, light as a feather, massive as a glacier. In ice, there is power!"
"Need a hammer? Gotta get your fix? I know a guy."
"Neither could I forget what I had read of these pits—that the sudden extinction of life formed no part of their most horrible plan."
"Neither the false God-Pharaoh nor his bugs will decide our fate."
"Never Surrender"
"Never brag about the latest wonder you've created, students. Chandler might be listening."
"Never cross a Pyknite, if you value your scalp."
"Never flinch from the truth."
"Never forget our ancestors. They have not forgotten us."
"Never get too attached to a weapon. You must allow a better one to find its way to you."
"Never leave the future to fate."
"Never let them take their eyes off you."
"Never look too deep, where the waters turn dark. What the sea has hidden there may not stay down forever."
"Never start a fight you can't finish."
"Never stop 'til you see your lance come out the other side."
"Never subtle nor cryptic is the reckoning of the mighty."
"Never taunt an embermage, 'What are you going to do about it?'"
"Never tell goblins to 'fire at will.'"
"Never thought I'd see the day I'd be wishing to see just a plain old werewolf."
"Never underestimate our enemy's strength, brutality, . . . or stupidity."
"Never underestimate the ability of natural forces to adapt to unnatural influences."
"New growth applies a healing poultice to wounds long scabbed over."
"New links are being added to the food chain on a daily basis."
"Next time, don't bother."
"Next to Grace is Reason, and Reason must be retained. If the web of Reason comes unwoven, madness will escape."
"Next to Law is Duty, and Duty must be obeyed. If the frame of Duty is broken, none shall weave life's fabric."
"Next!"
"Nice invention there. Looks real fragile."
"Nicely done, Jace. You always were good at disappearing acts."
"Nicol Bolas destroyed my world. I owe it to Skalla to celebrate all life, no matter how dangerous."
"Night wings sprinkled with dust Of a thousand soldiers dead And a thousand cities fallen."
"Ninjas can run across water, pull ladders from pockets, kill with a kiss, and slip between bricks. Pack of lies, I say."
"Nissa is not the only one with a deep connection to Zendikar's primal elements."
"Nissa will save the elves, but only the ones who have proved their worth."
"No amount of strength can help you overcome my trial. You must be ready to forgo your body and favor your mind."
"No bird soars too high, if he soars with his own wings."
"No doubt the arbiters would put you away, after all the documents are signed. But I will have justice now!"
"No doubt the arbiters would put you away, after all the documents are signed. But I will have justice now."
"No dwarf alive can best one of my crew dead."
"No emergency is so dire that it cannot be dealt with elegantly."
"No fact escapes me. Why do you think you can?"
"No fair Since when does a bug get ta munch on me?"
"No fair! Since when does a bug get ta munch on me?"
"No flame, no horror can sway me from my cause."
"No good will come from what you seek. Turn back now or suffer an ignoble death far from your home."
"No good will come of this."
"No half measures, no regrets. We'll tell no stories of this day. It will be as if it never existed at all."
"No life is without meaning. No living thing is too small to be strong."
"No longer am I shackled to antiquity. My new masters will etch a glorious future."
"No mage's deception can harm those who keep nature balanced."
"No matter how adept our artistic skill, our effigies can never hope to capture the vibrant beauty of a living elf. Perhaps that is truly why we mourn."
"No matter how busy my schedule gets, I always try to take time for that personal touch."
"No matter how far we push into Stensia, undeath will always remain in these lands."
"No matter how many I kill, there are always more to hunt. It makes me smile just to think about it."
"No matter how much a plane has suffered, there is a way to restore it."
"No matter how strong, an unarmed fighter is no more than a fool."
"No matter the cost, I must discover the source of these strange happenings."
"No matter where we cat warriors go in the world, those stupid slobberers find us."
"No matter who their fickle hearts worship, all mortals belong to one god in the end."
"No mockeries now for them; no prayers nor bells,  Nor any voice of mourning save the choirs,—  The shrill, demented choirs of wailing shells."
"No more blood shall be spilled to satisfy another's deluded lust for power."
"No more fear of death's oblivion—is this not the greatest treasure of all?"
"No more fear. No more failure. No more death. No more!"
"No more wretched fate is there than to waste away. If you are slain, your ghost may at least avenge itself upon your killer. But what release is there for one slain by Time?"
"No need for a hurda? How about these maps to recently discovered tombs? Or these vials of invisible potion? Very fancy . . ."
"No one can catch what won't be caught."
"No one can fight the tide forever."
"No one cares about pollution until they can see it."
"No one chooses to be stitched together into a skaab. If it could speak, it would beg for its own destruction."
"No one is born worthy."
"No one may fault an Elvish Ranger's heart, but the simplest frailty may fell even the proudest warrior."
"No one will ever ride me again, Gideon. Expect no further favors."
"No person was ever honored for what he received. Honor has been the reward for what he gave."
"No power is too great to be undone."
"No rest. No mercy. No matter what."
"No shadow remains for you to hide in."
"No shirt, no shoes, no service."
"No simple coin toss can solve this riddle. You must think and choose wisely."
"No single arrow can pierce an entire flock."
"No sooner had the beast collapsed under the blows of Takeno's sword than the earth rippled and the creature rose again to face him."
"No worthwhile reward is easily gained."
"No, I don't believe they have the proper permits for those, but I'm not going to be the one to ask."
"No, I insist—let me carry all that heavy jewelry."
"No, don't! Nal, it's me—"
"No, no, and ... no."
"No, you get the water. I ain't thirsty."
"Nobody asked you to butt in, Jace. But thanks."
"Nobody ever listens to my complaints! Not even when I use the listening stick."
"Nobody stands in one place better than a mogg."
"Nobody's seen the Lady of Videns for years. Poor dear, no companions at all in that old castle."
"None appreciate sun and shallows like those who have seen the depths."
"None can own the land's bounty. The gods made this world for all to share its riches. And I'm not just saying that because you caught me stealing your fruit."
"None may pass . . . for free."
"None of you are yet samurai. Defend your homes with honor, die for your cause, and perhaps then you will be worthy of the word."
"None of your history books mention me?"
"None will concede a place for us in this world. If it is not for us, neither shall it be for them. We rest not until they choke in its cold ashes."
"Nope, there's nothing here either. You guys go on ahead, I'll catch up in a minute. . . . Whoo hoo!"
"North and South meet and angels sing. Voices resound with a righteous ring."
"Not a surprise to see her on the podium. This paragon of tusk curvature is just the latest addition to the long championship lineage of Wildspeaker Ranch."
"Not again!"
"Not again."
"Not all Minotaurs are tribal. Some are freelance."
"Not all in our crop deserve the afterlife. We must leave the unworthy behind, Samut."
"Not all minotaurs are tribal. Some are freelance."
"Not all mortals fought the kami. The ogres revered the oni, while some humans made pacts based upon empty promises."
"Not all nightmares can be escaped by waking."
"Not all paths are found on the forest floor."
"Not bad, but I can think of a better use for that."
"Not even a roaring fire could thaw the chill it put in my heart."
"Not even my shadow knows where I am."
"Not even the magistrate in his lofty tower is out of our reach."
"Not everyone gets a second chance."
"Not my first edition of *The Advokist and the Urchin*!"
"Not someone to pick a fight with, unless you're fond of pain."
"Not the graveyard shift again!"
"Not too bright, but good enough for the job required—carrying and walking in a straight line."
"Nothin' beat surprise—'cept rock."
"Nothing against you. It's just that waiting for Consulate clearance was never really my thing."
"Nothing can stop the power of life—not even death."
"Nothing comes between me and my Didgeridoos™."
"Nothing endures but change."
"Nothing in nature goes to waste, not even the rotting corpse of a good-for-nothing, blood-sucking vampire."
"Nothing in this world, not even magic, likes to be caged."
"Nothing is more sacred than the gift of blood. Blessed are the vein that empties and the heart that is renewed."

"Nothing is the same anymore. The forests are not as lush, the waters not as pure, the air not as clear. Without the kami to direct and sustain the forces of nature, it's only a matter of time before we feel their neglect."
"Nothing ruins your day like a blazing zombie."
"Nothing will cool the fire in their blood. They are too far gone. We must keep them away from our towns at any cost."
"Now I know why they call it Shatterskull Pass. Rocks fell all night like hammers smashing an anvil. It's no wonder the giants are angry all the time."

"Now I lay me down to sleep—
What are *you* starin' at?"
"Now I'm thirsty."
"Now everyone knows what you are."
"Now is not the time for your light to fade."
"Now is the hour. Ours is the duty. For victory and family—charge!"
"Now isn't that better?"
"Now listen closely, my young gob. There are many ways to eat pimple bugs, but I say the best way is all smashed together between two slug chips."
"Now that I have your attention, perhaps I can tell you of the Order."
"Now that I've dealt with your little toys, I can focus on the real problem: you."
"Now that's a fashion statement."
"Now that's the Chandra I've been waiting to see."
"Now there's something you don't see every day."
"Now your staff is as twisted as your soul."
"Now, *that's* a zombie!"
"Now, little fighter, show me you deserved this second chance."
"Now, that's a fashion statement."
"Nyx may belong to the gods, but the skies of Theros are ours."
"O Great Captain, all is lost. They tunneled, they burrowed, they trenched. They sapped the strength of our defenses."
"O to be a dragon . . . of silkworm size or immense . . ."
"O! call back yesterday, bid time return."
"O! it is excellent  To have a giant's strength, but it is tyrannous  To use it like a giant."
"O! it is excellent To have a giant's strength, but it is tyrannous To use it like a giant."
"Oathbreaker, I cast you out!"
"Obey!"
"Obviously, the Firemind's mission is worth more than a few goblins."
"Occasionally, there are those who refuse to appreciate all that the God-Pharaoh provides for us."

"Odum and Broadbark were the only beings mighty enough to challenge the giant Moran the Destroyer. Their battle lasted a hundred dawns, until Moran became so exhausted that he fell into namesleep. He awoke as Moran the Gardener."

"The Lord of the Wastes must be destroyed; I am bound to this destiny by the chains of fate. If only Gerrard would see his part."
"The Mardu are like the gore swine. We are wild, hunt in packs, and rarely clean the blood from our blades."
"The Mardu rush headlong toward extinction. We ensure the longevity of our clan by protecting our territory, not rampaging through it."
"The Matrons are kindly souls, but don't ask one for an ale."
"The Matrons still say Serra is coming back. I bet she never even existed."
"The Mercadians are too busy looking down on us to see us coming."
"The Moriok are fools. They try so hard to gain my favor. All I want is for them to die quickly, to join the ranks of the nim."
"The Mountain gave us the Flame to Kradak to light the furnaces of his people's hearts. The wanderers became Keldons, and he the first warlord."
"The Mwonvuli Jungle has given the darkness teeth for tearing the gift of life from the weak."
"The Na Plateau is lost. Do not ask what happened, and never return there."
"The Ojutai are my favorite victims. They have so much knowledge to lose."
"The Okiba Gang! Night-cursed thieves and assassins! I've had enough of their meddling! Triple the guard!"
"The Origin Query will wait. We must ensure we survive to return to it."
"The Phyrexians are vulnerable. Do not despair. We will prevail!"
"The Phyrexians have progressed,"
"The Rakdos know little of technology, but they definitely know how to push buttons."
"The Reito Massacre was a testament to the kami's unstoppable power. The human defenders might as well have been moths battling a forest fire."
"The River Heralds carve spells into jade, hoping to steer us from our course. But what right do they have to keep us from that which once was ours?"
"The River flows. My soul returns."
"The Roil is destructive, but not random. It's Zendikar's way of revealing secrets."
"The Roil may be unpredictable, but it is not uncontrollable."
"The Selesnya are gathering armies. Do you still believe they aren't preparing for war?"
"The Shaman waved the staff, and the land itself went mad."
"The Shamans? Ha! They are mere craven cows not capable of true magic."
"The Shifting Wastes provide our clan eternal protection. It is our duty to return the favor."
"The Silumgar creep around our borders and infiltrate our aeries. We must remain ever watchful."
"The Silumgar hide behind the deadly wildlife of their swamps. They'd rather scheme in their jungle palaces than face us."
"The Simic offer a prize to any biomancer who can breed a krasis to match a griffin in the air. It's never been claimed."
"The Skirk Ridge has many wonderful things to discover—like escape routes."
"The Soul selects her own Society— Then—shuts the Door—"
"The Spirit Crafters sing of all our people. They sing of those lost, of those found, and of those who are yet to be."
"The Sultai take our dead, so we shall take their living!"
"The Tangle loans you life. Spend it well."
"The Tangle reaches out to itself constantly, forming new connections. We must follow its example."
"The Tenth has always been my home. This city is constantly embroiled in one crisis or another, but I'm determined to protect my piece."
"The Thaw brings flooding, disease, and death. We will do all in our power to bring frigid peace back to the world."
"The Uktabi efreet and I have something in common: both of our mothers wanted to give us back."
"The White Shield is not the burnished metal you lash to your forearm but the conviction that burns in your chest."
"The White-Shielders think their code justifies their actions. In truth it only binds their hands."
"The Wojek defend the laws. We defend the people."
"The academy educates; I employ. It's a perfect arrangement."
"The admixture of bitterwort in the viral brew has produced most favorable results."
"The ainok are wild dogs, not fit to join us around the fire."
"The air filled with dust and the sound of wingbeats. The mothriders had joined the fray."
"The air stirred as if fanned by angels' wings, and the enemy was turned aside."
"The alliances were already frayed. All we do is find the loose threads and pluck."
"The altar does nothing; the device is crushed under the weight of its own impurity."
"The amber of the tree and the blood of my veins are the same."
"The amber sun smokes with fury, gazing on foes that gather like ants invading our home. We are ready! Blade and claw strike as one."

"The amphin have long built their society in secret. While surface dwellers squabbled over trivial borders, they patiently expanded, building their ammonite temple-caves. Now amphin priests eye the shore, and amphin hunters gird for war."
"The animal spirits are the Ancestor's grandchildren. Remember them."
"The answer to life should never be death; it should always be more life, wrapped tight around us like precious silks."
"The answer's in here somewhere!"
"The answers are here. This is the way through the trial."
"The appearance of these warped stones throughout the provinces is too pervasive to be random. More evidence is needed to determine the reason behind them."
"The archon fell like a star from the sky, meeting the rising sun at the horizon's edge."
"The arrow strikes one bird down, but the flock remains."
"The aven are heralds of divinity. The greatest glory is to join them in the sky."
"The awestruck birds gazed at Wonder. Slowly, timidly, they rose into the air."
"The battle at Ganzan Pass was a testament to human endurance. The untrained and frightened group escaped three legions of kami, leaving more than their share of slain foes in their wake."
"The battle is won. There's work to be done.  The Blessed Sleep must wait.  A fiend is about. It stalks the devout.  I'll save them from my fate."
"The battlefield is cluttered enough. Be still."
"The bear is never cautious—which is why it wasn't born a human."
"The beasts of the wild are my senses. It is through their eyes that all knowledge shall come to me."
"The beauty of it is they never see it coming. Ever."
"The beauty of mental attacks is that your victims never remember them."
"The bells may one day ring as an anthem of our own end."
"The benefits of peace far outweigh the pride of Generals."
"The best answers solve more than one riddle."
"The best armor is to keep out of range."
"The best construction makes the most satisfying destruction."
"The best denials are simply that: a beginning and end unchanged, a dream with no memory."
"The best expedition would be an entire team of me."
"The best foresight is hindsight."
"The best lessons are not the ones I teach. They are the ones the pupils realize for themselves."
"The best servants are made from those who died without a scratch."
"The best skaab are more powerful and more beautiful than the sum of their parts."
"The best skaabs are more powerful and more beautiful than the sum of their parts."
"The best spot to hook one is right behind the gills."
"The best things in life are free. Money, for instance."
"The best way over the mountain is through."
"The best way to keep a secret is to forget it."
"The best way to learn from a book on pyromancy is to burn it."
"The best way to teach is by example."
"The bigger they are, the faster they rot."
"The bird of wonder dies, the maiden phoenix, Her ashes new-create another heir As great in admiration as herself."
"The bird wore the form of a man, bereft of filigree. Why do the Texts not speak of it?"
"The blood of Dromoka and the blood of my veins are the same."
"The blood of Kiyomaro flows in my veins. He did not let Eiganjo fall and neither shall I."
"The blood of the enemy is a sacrament. The strength it gives is proof that our cause is just."
"The blood of the forest is beholden to no one."
"The blood of the weak shall be the ink with which we scribe great Yawgmoth's glorious name."
"The blood of your ancestors ran heavy on this soil. Now it's your turn to sacrifice for the glory of Shiv."
"The blood on my hands is merely proof of my ambition."
"The blood ritual is complete. The end approaches."
"The body is a temple with a foundation of sand."
"The bog doesn't give a stinking bubble about your title, wealth, or piety. It's just hungry."
"The bonds of bushido will draw the dishonored back someday, and I will be there waiting."
"The bonds of loyalty can tie one to the grave."
"The bones of allies grant wisdom. The bones of enemies grant strength. The bones of dragons grant life eternal."
"The bones of the past will tell their tales—if you know how to speak their language."
"The bravest warriors take the shortest path to victory, whatever that path may be."
"The brood lineages unfolded across the world, each patterned after one of three progenitors, each a study in mindless consumption."
"The burst of strength brought on by this plague should not be mistaken for a sign of renewed health."
"The caliph was so intelligent he could not remember what he knew."
"The call came, spell-borne through mortar and stone to the ear of every soldier. The call came, and the advantage was ours."
"The call of the Blessed Sleep is not so strong as the call to protect those in need."
"The cannon wasn't aimed at you!"
"The cathars have their swords, the inquisitors their axes. I prefer the 'diplomatic' approach."
"The cathars killed my skaabs down below. Let's see how high their swords can reach."
"The centaurs are truly free. Never will they be tamed by temptation or controlled by fear. They live in total harmony, a feat not yet achieved by our kind."
"The ceremony ended with a voice from the shadows, a voice with vast, ominous power."
"The chain fit my neck perfectly, but my heart fluttered with chills as the cool metal came to rest against my chest. I closed the clasp and waited, silent."
"The changing kind suffers as we do. We must join as one to quench our tyrants!"
"The chest cavity is cleared of useless meat. I know just what to do with the space."
"The church looks down on binding spirits into armor, but now I can look down on them."
"The city is overrun. I would say burn it to the ground, but that won't be necessary."
"The clashing warriors turned to face O-Kagachi, the greatest kami, and their sigh of awe was their last breath."
"The clouds came alive and dove to the earth! Hooves flashed among the dark army, who fled before the spectacle of fury."
"The clouds obey my whims, and you'll obey theirs."
"The clues have begun to reveal a truth I hesitate to accept."
"The colossal thing rumbled over the ridge, tree husks crumbling before it. The ones we were already fighting howled as it came, their muscles suddenly surging, and we knew it was time to flee."
"The common folk are ceaselessly active. The fields are fertile and the soil productive, and neither flood nor drought plagues us."
"The common folk call it the breaking of the crust or the spilling of fire. Geomancers call it target practice."
"The constellations form a tapestry of light that traces my people's broken history. Day and night, I feel their glittering presence calling me to weave the pattern whole."
"The construction of a defense is not accomplished by adding bricks."
"The cooling climate forced the Elves to experiment with new food sources."

"The cooling climate introduced a new threat to Vodalia: the Homarids. Once a minor nuisance, they thrived in the changing environment. Their ceaseless attacks strained Vodalia's defenses to their limit, eventually overwhelming the empire."
"The cornfields promise a good yield this season."
"The cost of your opposition will be extracted from your wits."
"The cracks widened, the shell crumbled, and Valor spread throughout the land."
"The creature we fought in the western waste was doubly dangerous: mortally wounded, it rebounded and attacked again."
"The crossing demands singular focus. Your life consists of these ropes, these hooks, and these rocky crags. Your past is miles below."
"The curious merely amass knowledge. The ambitious use it."
"The curse is broken."
"The cyclops shrugged off savage blows, but casual insults made him weep."
"The danger in cultivating massive plants caught the elves by surprise."
"The darkness crawls with vampires and ghouls, but we are not without allies."
"The day is mine! I sent three such creatures against my foe, then watched as my magefire popped her soldiers like overripe spleenfruits."
"The day of Spirits; my soul's calm retreat  Which none disturb!"
"The day of Spirits; my soul's calm retreat  Which none disturb"
"The day of spirits; my soul's calm retreat Which none disturb!"
"The day will come when the righteous warrior faces a battle she cannot win. She will greet that day as she has any other."

"The days before the war were filled with strange portents: scouts and herders spoke of villages reduced to ash, of farmers taken from their fields, and of foul beasts roaming the plains in packs. I know, for I spoke to them all."
"The dead have it easy. They suffer no more. If breaking their rest helps the living, so be it."
"The dead make good soldiers. They can't disobey orders, never surrender, and don't stop fighting when a random body part falls off."
"The dead make good soldiers. They can't disobey orders, they never surrender, and they don't stop fighting when a random body part falls off."
"The dead may be beyond the law, but speaking the wisdom of the dead will afford no protection!"
"The dead perform all the work here—farming, building, teaching, even embalming their fellow mummies. The living need do nothing but train. What system could be more perfect?"
"The dead whisper to the living. If you listen, you will learn."
"The deal was struck and the favor had been done. And so, under the cover of night, the debt was paid."
"The demons don't care if we mutter niceties and act out ceremonies. Just kill him."
"The derelor's greatest contribution to the Ebon Hand was the inspirational effect its creator's execution had upon the other thrull breeders."
"The desert asked the Ancestor for children, and the antelope were born."
"The desire for its magic horn inspires such bloodthirsty greed that all who see the unicorn will kill to possess it."
"The dim resort to violence, for which the nimble prepare."
"The distraction of your life has ended. Now your service begins."
"The dragon is a perfect marriage of power and the will to use it."
"The dragon wing of night o'erspreads the earth."
"The dragonlords rule the tempests of the skies. Here in the wastes, the storms are mine to command."
"The dragons thought they were too strong to be tamed, too large to fall. And where are they now?"
"The drakes are practice. We may one day need to bring down a sky swallower, or maybe even Rakdos himself."
"The drawing of maps is fruitless in the west near the ice walls; the very earth is formless."
"The dream does not end until I say so."
"The dreams of a child fulfilled: The wind on my brow, the air 'neath my feet."
"The druids would be better off if they spent more time in the lab and less time watching trees grow."
"The duel was going badly for me, and Zur thought I was finished. He boasted that he would eat my soul—but all he ate were his words."
"The dust beneath our feet was once part of a mighty civilization. Shall we too provide the path for a future generation?"
"The earth shook, the sky rained fire, and it seemed the world was ending."
"The echo of silence is music to my ears."
"The edges of the Quicksilver Sea run dark with the spread of the Mephidross. Two more aerial passes before I can be sure what I'm seeing . . ."
"The educated mind is heavy with lore and knowledge. It's also the most likely to collapse under its own weight."
"The eerie, wailing Hymn caused insanity even in hardened warriors."
"The efreet is a striding storm with a voice that crackles like fire."
"The elders say Zendikar has no safe, peaceful places. How would they know? They've never looked."
"The elders say that if the intruders discovered the secret of the golden city, it would mean an end to our people."
"The element of surprise only works when it's backed up by a bolt between the eyes."
"The elements understand better than anyone that actions speak louder than words."
"The elves are right: Death inevitably leads to life. But the truly powerful don't just experience this cycle. They control it."
"The elves can hide better than most can look."
"The elves claim the canopy. The nacatl claim the mountains. I suppose you think we ought to stay on the jungle floor?"
"The elves may try to confine us, but they will learn that our blazing spirit can never be suppressed."
"The elves tend the forest, and the forest sustains the elves. My role is to ensure that the cycle continues."
"The elves use treefolk to drive us away. It is time to remove their tools."
"The embers of our homes still smolder, and already the villages of Kjeldor burn in retaliation. What they have started, we will finish."
"The empire belongs to no one man but to all in the empire. He who has virtue shall possess it."
"The empire, long united, must divide, and long divided, must unite."
"The end is justified in being mean. Or something like that."
"The end justifies the means. What do I care if I rule over the dead rather than over the living? The dead ask fewer questions."
"The enemy has been destroyed, sir. So have the forest, the city, your palace, your dog . . ."
"The enemy is getting too close! Quick! Inflate the toad!"
"The entire murder scene was covered in dripping, oozing slime. No need for a soothsayer to solve that one."
"The essence of a lawful society is swift deterrence."
"The expected way through the trial is far too tedious."
"The face of Light will shine upon them, and they will know war no more."
"The face of mediocrity is wrapped in anointed linen. Aspire to a better end."
"The faerie plucked an acorn off the ground. One knight's quest was about to come to a bitter end."
"The faith of Serra is borne on wings of hope."
"The faithful don't succumb to terror, nor are they ruled by passion. They adhere to order, for order is life."
"The false god Xenagos treats the whole world as his rollick site. If his whims are left unchecked, Theros will be reduced to rubble and ashes."
"The family is a tree, and in times of need, every branch can be a weapon."
"The fangren fight without comfort of any kind. We can ask no less of ourselves."
"The fatal flaw in every plan is the assumption that you know more than your enemy."
"The fever clouds the mind as it energizes the body. Both will pass in time."
"The few of us who survived were denied entry to our camp for two days—so like the pox were the marks we bore."
"The few remaining pieces from this period suggest the Dwarves eventually made weapons and armor out of everything, even children's toys."
"The fiends have fled. Well, good riddance. Nothing I like more than an empty lair."
"The fiercest loyalties are earned in battle."
"The fifth wind of ascension is Exalter, fulfilling Keld's destiny."
"The filthy towns of Kjeldor are no place for anyone to live. Fyndhorn is our home now."
"The final stage of the illness: delirium, convulsions, and death."
"The finest minions know what I need without me ever saying a thing."
"The finest offering of night is not stealth but daring."
"The finest pawns are those with pawns of their own."
"The fires of invention burn in all of us. I fight for the freedom to unleash those flames."
"The first birth celebrates life. The second birth mocks it."
"The first blow is the most important. It often negates the need for a second."
"The first caravan has passed safely through the Karplusan Mountains without incident, forging a trade route to Balduvia. Kjeld himself would never have believed it"
"The first rule of politics can be learned from a lowly hornbettle: it is wise to cultivate powerful friends."
"The first stage of the illness: rash and nausea."
"The first time was amusing, but now you're getting tiresome."
"The first wind of ascension is Forger, burning away impurity."
"The fishers will throw out their nets and draw them back filled with dust."
"The flame paints a bright wheel on the sky, then shifts into a stabbing spark. The enemy falls; the smoke of victory rises. — "
"The fleeting shadows of his primitive self have all but vanished."
"The flesh is a casket for the soul."
"The flies were bothering me."
"The floor of the sea is paved with the shattered remnants of vessels that navigated its surface unwelcomed."
"The flow is diverted. Your path is clear. What are you waiting for—the cave to bid you welcome?"
"The folk of the Karplusan Mountains are impossible to ambush."
"The fools thought me dead. But I built an empire inside my tomb."
"The forest has as many eyes as leaves."
"The forest is my cover and I hold it close. In such a tight embrace, there is no room for wickedness."
"The forest surrounding the Vess estate became the Caligo Morass, a vast bog stalked by horrors too terrible to name."
"The forest will surround you with its life if you are still and calm."
"The forests have succumbed to ruin, but the spirit of Krosa remains alive and vital in these devouring spores."
"The forward flame-kin are popping. We have incoming!"
"The foul entities of the Uuserk swamp had never before dared to spread their influence to the very heart of Zhalfir."
"The fourth wind of ascension is Anointer, deifying the worthy."
"The further into the future I look, the less certain my vision. Even now, the middle distance is obscured by fire."
"The fury in the lion's eye; the patience in the hippo's yawn; the pride within the griffin's cry are one within the iron tusk's stride."
"The future is a snake, devouring your life backwards through time. And when you die, believe me, it doesn't stop feeding."
"The giant wept tears of embers for the deaths of his allies."
"The giants follow the flow of aether, and twice a year it leads them through here. Lesson learned. More clearance is needed."
"The gift of life must be freely given. Anything less would diminish us all."
"The gleam of rubies and my brothers and sisters by my side . . . what more could I want?"
"The goblins are in charge of maintenance? Why not just set it on fire now and call it a day?"
"The gods here may walk among the people, but they are not with them."
"The gods of Theros are born of the expectations and beliefs of mortals. If I have found godhood, what does that say about their true desires?"
"The gods think of us as insects. Perhaps there is wisdom in that."
"The gods used their feathers to paint all the colors of the world."
"The good don't sit and wait for the evil to act. They prepare to defend. They prepare to punish."
"The good news is that the migrating drakes are no longer a problem."
"The good news is, we figured out how the wand works. The bad news is, we figured out how the wand works."
"The good of society matters much more than the inconvenience of a few."
"The greatest gift Dromoka gives is the ability to fly without wings."
"The greatest honor is to feed Atarka."
"The ground grew swampy; hooves and claws sank into the marshy earth. Snarls of rage and bleats of despair echoed through the trees as the waters grew higher and higher."
"The ground polluted floats with human gore, And human carnage taints the dreadful shore Fly swift the dangerous coast: let every ear Be stopp'd against the song! 'tis death to hear!"
"The guilds each believe its way is right, but their ways only bring blood to Ravnica's streets and tears to Ravnica's families."
"The guilds promise to provide safety. I prefer to make my own."
"The hand of Keranos can be seen in every rumbling storm cloud. Best not to stand where he points."
"The hard part isn't landing in the saddle. The hard part is leaping before you see it."
"The harder they try to extinguish my faith, the brighter it burns in the darkness."
"The harder we press forward, the harder Krosa pushes us back."
"The harder you push, the stronger we become."
"The hardest thing is finding the right ingredients."
"The healers of Bant are second to none. I owe then a great deal for their tutelage."
"The heat in our hearts sometimes rises to the surface."
"The hermit dies. The outcast dies. The lone wolf dies. Only those who stick together survive this world."
"The highway of fear is the shortest route to defeat."
"The hive shimmered, and its walls seemed a living mirror."
"The horizon is the perpetual ideal, the constant promise of hope."
"The horror The horror"
"The hour of Dusk is come."
"The hour of your redemption is here. . . . Rally to me. . . . rise and strike. Strike at every favorable opportunity. For your homes and hearths, strike!"
"The hum of the universe is never off-key."
"The humans and their gods never blessed me. Only the pride deserves my allegiance."
"The humans are useful in their way, but they must be commanded as the builder commands the stone. Be soft with them, and they will become soft."
"The husk splits like a madman's smile And mystery steps forth."
"The hypocrisy of these elves is thicker than steel—destroying 'unnatural metal' with their own enchanted swords."
"The identifying ornamental growths of alpha thallids may be hereditary, or catalyzed by some chemical signal."
"The ignorant fear change; the wise use it as a weapon."
"The infection has spread farther than we could glimpse from the heights of Taj-Nar."
"The injury was being caught between this world and our own; the insult was to find walls within."
"The invaders cloak themselves in the shadows of dusk. Aerosaurs hide in the brilliance of the noonday sun."
"The invasion has awoken slumbering mountains,"
"The jeweler, the potter, the smith . . . They all imbue a bit of their souls into their creations. The kami destroy that crafted mortal shell and absorb the soul within."
"The judges really put them through their paces, but they prevailed. I think they even impressed Head Judge Tezzeret."
"The jungle was here before any city. It will be here after the last city falls."
"The kami struck with gouts of fire, showers of rock, and the combined rage of the spirit world. Only Eiganjo Castle remained standing, glistening untouched in the sun."
"The key to unlocking this puzzle is within you."
"The key to winning any fight is simply staying alive."
"The king would die for the realm. I would not hesitate to do the same for him."
"The knights charged forward on wings of wind, and the necromancer's horde roared in helpless rage."
"The land already knows its destiny. I simply ask it to share the tale with me."
"The land belongs to nature as far as our eyes can see. The higher we climb, the more we can see."
"The land gives of itself. Its abundance provides, even in times of chaos."
"The land gives up little, but we are masters of persuasion."
"The land grows only where the kami will it."
"The land has been gracious enough to let you tread upon her for years. That privilege is about to end."
"The land here seems to go out of its way to kill you."
"The land is not dead, merely sick. I will nurse it back to health."
"The land is swollen with mana, cursed relics, and secrets. If you puncture it, you never know what will burst out."
"The land is weary. Even Skyshroud is depleted. We must find another source of mana—one that is growing despite our withering world."
"The land putrefied at its touch, turned into an oily bile in seconds."
"The land shall beg for drink and curse the rain that follows."
"The lands of the God-Pharaoh are suffused with his breath."
"The landscape shimmered and I felt a chill breeze. When my vision cleared, I found myself alone among the corpses of my fallen friends."
"The large brass claws worn by some Sarpadian Orc tribes were among the least feared weapons ever known."
"The lasting effects are invariably fatal."
"The law has its place—as a footnote in my spellbook."
"The least of gods shall tower over the mightiest of mortals, and death shall reign over all."
"The light of a felidar's horns can give even an Eldrazi pause."
"The light of an angel's glance is warm, but her fixed stare blinds and burns."
"The light of beauty protects our journeys through darkness."
"The light of my master's guidance traverses all boundaries, even those separating life and death."
"The light of the Ancestor will scour the taint of darkness from the land."
"The little thopters seemed lonely up here, so I thought I'd join them."
"The living are born small and weak. The dead rise ready to serve. The choice is obvious."
"The living cannot understand the benefits of death."
"The living don't ever stay living, and the dead don't always stay dead."
"The longer it's caged, the madder it gets."
"The longer the journey, the more one learns."
"The lotus takes root where body and mind intersect. It blooms when body and mind become one."
"The love of nature . . . is a furious, burning, physical greed. . . ."
"The maaka remain loyal to us in this time of strife. We don't even have to feed them—our enemies do."
"The magic at the heart of all living things can bear awe-inspiring fruit."
"The maze seems to fight us at every turn, resisting our efforts to solve it."
"The meadow sprang up beneath me, and I perceived a path from our people's defeat to our highest glory."
"The meek inherit nothing."
"The meek shall fight as one, and they shall overcome even the greatest of foes."
"The memory of your existence will fade like the final stars of morning."
"The mere sight of our undead allies sickens me. What unholy bargain have you struck?"

"The merfolk of the Pearl Trident have risen from the waves since the earliest days, at times allies to humans, other times enemies. Now their power is cresting again, and who can say which way the new tide will flow."
"The mighty rely solely on their strength. They are shocked when we do the same."
"The mind: a great weapon and an even greater weakness."
"The mist whispers to those who know it to be more than a mundane fog."
"The mists coalesced into silent warriors. We charged them and broke through their lines, only to see them swirl and re-form behind us."
"The mongoose blew out its candle and was asleep in bed before the room went dark."
"The monks of the North Tree rarely saw their kodama until the Kami War, when it woke like a slumbering, angry bear."
"The monks of the South Tree had always reveled beneath their kodama's friendly gaze. During the Kami War, this gaze became fierce and full of hate."
"The monster was gaining on them. Twice it had found them. There was only one place let to hide."
"The more I see of this place, the less I want to."
"The more dangerous, the better."
"The more kami that passed through the veil that separated them from our world, the weaker that veil became, threatening to tear into tatters at the slightest pressure."
"The more our numbers grow, the more I gain hope that Volrath and his cursed stronghold will one day fall."
"The more secrets you have, the more easily you become my pawn."
"The mortal world is a grove of sweet fruit, and I am ready to harvest it."
"The most brilliant stars are not born of Nyx."
"The most disappointing thing about learning telepathy is finding out how boring people really are."
"The most elegant solutions are found in nature. You just have to know where to look."
"The most enlightened mages create beauty from violence."
"The most impressive performances can be done only once."
"The most insidious thing in the world is nonsense that sounds just plausible enough to listen to."
