"There's no more time for secluded study. Answers are there only for those with the courage to take them."
"There's no need to sound the alarm. You are minding your post admirably. I am authorized. All is well."
"There's no question that these waters are treacherous, but if there's one thing I've learned in all my years of sailing . . ."
"There's no reason to buy a new one when I've got the tools to fix the one you've got."
"There's no sense arguing with insanity."
"There's no such thing as 'impenetrable.'"
"There's no time to calm it down! Run!"
"There's no trade without trust."
"There's not enough salt in all of Nephalia to wither that thing."
"There's nothing I like better than watching a street full of soldiers kicking down the doors of the guilty and the impure."
"There's nothing like a sudden shock to clarify one's thoughts."
"There's nothing like the high seas to clear your head or escape pursuers."
"There's nothing to worry about."
"There's only one route from Kessig into Stensia. Unless you come with me."
"There's plenty of fire to go around."
"There's something peculiar about the cats today."
"There's something peculiar about the rain today."
"There's very little that escapes me, Greven. And you will escape very little if you fail."
"There's wisdom to be gained in death—whether it be one's own or someone else's."
"These Gruul skin-runes—discern whether their patterns evoke streets, leylines, or both. You have four days."
"These Sorcerers always seem to have another surprise up their sleeves."
"These alleys are not safe. Come, I can guide you back to the market square."
"These are your streets. Defend them! This is your neighborhood. Honor it! This is your city. Save it!"
"These bracers were worn by my father and by his mother before him. Boggart fangs have shattered on them. Cinder flames have withered at their touch. While I wear them, the safehold will not fall."
"These creatures offer new challenges in the scrutiny of entrails."
"These days, soldiers never stick around long enough for a proper healing. They just want me to knit them up so they can hurry back to the fight."
"These days, there's no shortage of food for the nulls of Guul Draz."
"These eyes have shown me the flaws of flesh."
"These guards are the most disciplined military unit in the city. They couldn't fight their way out of a broom closet, but they've got discipline."
"These halls are sacred. You will be silent."
"These horn-haters say no gods but theirs exist. I say let him find out for himself—right now!"
"These kavu are so stubborn they even refuse to die."
"These kids today with their collector numbers and their newfangled tap symbol. Twenty Black Lotuses and twenty Plague Rats. Now that's real Magic."
"These moonless, foreign skies keep me in thrall. Dark whispers echo in the night, and I cannot resist."
"These nezumi, they disgust me. The things they will do for money no other thinking creature would consider. This, of course, makes them useful beyond words."
"These pirates must answer for their ancestors, who renounced the Church of Dusk and sailed from Torrezon as heretics."
"These polearms were supposed to help!"
"These rains cannot quench; they carve the land's face like a scalpel on flesh."
"These runes are tough enough without the distraction,"
"These sailors on our shores are like the dinosaurs that plunder eggs from nests. They live on the labors of others."
"These storied halls are under my protection."
"These things will protect you while I'm gone, remind you of my love for you."
"These, of all spells, must have common components I can isolate and use."
"They appreciate my handiwork. I hear their joy in every scream."
"They are 'between' in every way."
"They are bred to suffer and born to die. Much like humans."
"They are called 'Mi'uto,' which means 'one use.'"
"They are called 'fowl' for a reason."
"They are called Eternals. They will never stop."
"They are deadly, and they are loyal. We can spare them a little blood."
"They are fighters as fine as any Knight they carry."
"They are gentle herbivores, despite their size. Approach cautiously, and hum a tune to let them know you mean no harm."
"They are like their vedalken masters: untouchable, aloof, and omnipresent."
"They are quick to offer advice, those whose mistakes doomed them to undeath. How can I not listen to the wisdom of failure?"
"They are small, but they always want more. Learn from them."
"They are the eyes of the Baron, and they know your fears."
"They are the finest companions in the realm. Swift, clever, and easily trained to hunt intruders."
"They are the first to raise the alarm when the levelers attack, and the first to risk their lives to defend the pride."
"They aren't helping the forges. Send them to the surface."
"They aren't the brightest or the quickest of Giants. For that matter, the same holds true if you compare them to rocks."
"They believe they're driving us back, but we're leading them to their doom."
"They bind us with their laws. We free ourselves with nature's fist."
"They can't even comprehend nature. How could they improve it?"
"They can't feel pain. They just wiggle 'cause they're scared."
"They certainly are well protected. Too bad for them they're not well balanced."
"They come because I call. They stay because I listen."
"They come to drink, to bathe, and—I believe—to play."
"They don't even feel the cut. I'm ordering a drink in a nearby tavern before anyone notices something's wrong."
"They don't make them like they used to."
"They don't move much, but then again, if you get caught in its web, it has all the time in the world to get to you."
"They don't move, do they?"
"They employ a foul sort of teamwork."
"They encircled our patrol with the stealth of snakes, corralling us like livestock."
"They exist only so long as the living take no notice."
"They gave their lives to strengthen the Order's armies, until they declined this honor in favor of joining the Thrull Rebellion."
"They groaned, they stirred, they all uprose, Nor Spake, nor moved their eyes; It had been strange, even in a dream, To have seen those dead men rise."
"They groaned, they stirred, they all uprose, Nor spake, nor moved their eyes; It had been strange, even in a dream, To have seen those dead men rise."
"They had it coming."
"They have forsaken their vows. The edict of the Circle demands their voices be silenced."
"They have knives for every soul."
"They have long kept us under attack, but we do not lack for ammunition. The very bodies of our foes arm us against them."
"They infiltrated deep into the enemy camp under cover of darkness . . . and dirt."
"They killed my family to deny me a future. They fed on my ancestors to deny me a past."
"They knew Bantau was lost when, to hide the pearl he had found on the beach, he swallowed it—and soon grew wings."
"They make it clear we are nothing to them."
"They may show up with the wrong thigh bone or mandible, but they always show up."
"They no longer care about their own suffering. Show them something worse."
"They play by spitting fire at each other. Don't be offended if one gives you a love-scorch."
"They put bars on these noble beasts and then wonder why werewolves target our towns."
"They ride our trails as if they were designed to,"
"They said obey and you'll be happy. They said you'll be safe. But we're not safe. We're not happy. And we will not obey."
"They say Head Judge Tezzeret will be reviewing every invention at the Fair. I made sure to build something that will stand out."
"They say a Zhalfirin archer can split the eye of a griffin. Nonsense, of course: they have no faith to guide their darts."
"They say a Zhalfirin archer can split the eye of a griffin. Nonsense, of course; they have no faith to guide their darts."
"They say only the good die young. Obviously, you are one of the exceptions."
"They say that perfection is unattainable, but they say that about flight too."
"They say the eyes are the windows to the soul. I like to break windows and take what's inside."
"They search for treasures that wash up from the depths. Tracking one could lead you to riches. Or in circles."
"They seek to break us. Let us show them our strength!"
"They serve the world best on a platter with shallots and onions."
"They shall drink sorrow's dregs. They shall kill those whom once they loved."
"They shall give us all they have as penance for their resistance. Their ships. Their goods. Their rebellious blood."
"They shall kill those whom once they loved."
"They share more than their thoughts. We must shatter their link quickly!"
"They started it."
"They tell us the wilds are ours, then they brick them over. They can lie to our faces but not to our fists."
"They thought their fortress impregnable . . . until we marched up with ours, and blocked out the sun."
"They were once our brothers and sisters."
"They were your friends, your family, your clan. They want only to welcome you."
"They weren't part of my plan, but Gaea insisted."
"They who challenge a minotaur enjoy the taste of their own blood."
"They who fall singing the battle hymn of Benalia go not unavenged."
"They won't be winning any beauty pageants, but they'll do the trick."
"They won't see your shadow or hear your breath, but they will feel your blade."
"They wouldn't sell their own families—at least, not for cheap."
"They'd pour out of the warrens to make war (and to make room for the littering matrons)."
"They'll never see me coming."
"They're a hardy bunch, but I'd still bet that they just slept through the worst of the cold times."
"They're as much like plants as animals. Leave them unchecked, and they'll choke out all other forms of life."
"They're easy enough to find. Question is, are you sure you want to find one?"
"They're in the walls! Can't you hear them?"
"They're not easily trained. Fortunately, they already know how to kill."
"They're not half as fierce if they don't see you coming."
"They're not worth much, but they're easy to catch."
"They're not your friends; they despise you. I'm the only one you can count on. Trust me."
"They're numerous, attack in swarms, and are always hungry. No wonder we rats hold such a kinship with them."
"They're searching in the same direction we are. And for the same thing, I'll wager."
"They're smart enough to understand that war means lots of carrion."
"They're so much more willing to parley once they're hanging from a boom by the ankle!"
"They're still here?! The cockroach may have finally met its match."
"They're ugly, and they're in my way."
"They've got eyes inside my head!"
"Thick hides and layered armor won't help when I freeze you from the inside out."
"Things are going to change around here."
"Things were popping like corn in a skillet. Olly landed in the pig pen with his prize sow on top of him, both squealin' like boggarts."
"Think of the problems we'll face if you uproot entire continents,"
"Think of them not as failures but as works in progress."
"Thirsty?"
"This 'standing windstorm' can hold us off indefinitely? Ridiculous!"
"This abomination never belonged in our world. I'm merely setting it free."
"This air feels so heavy and thick. There are no winds to speak of. I fear the knowledge that comes from a place like this."
"This armor transcends the limitations of mere flesh and bone."
"This aura threatens the sanctity of your soul. Wrenching it free won't be easy on either of us. If you're ready, we'll begin."
"This can't be Jamuraa. We could not have failed her this badly . . . ."
"This close to Rimewind Keep, no avalanche is nature's doing."
"This creature has innate perceptiveness. It knows when to rise and when to vanish into the tides."
"This creature is inadequate. Send it to the splicers for innovation."
"This day will end in death, but not the one you hoped for. This day will end in victory, but not the one you expected."
"This feels a little more like home."
"This forest means more to the druids than their own kin. The loss of a tree is like the loss of a child."
"This imprint was the familiar of a friend."
"This is Mileva, in the Tenth. We've got an elf in the plaza with a chip on her shoulder. Actually, it's more of a morningstar."
"This is a battle of pawns, for the highest stakes imaginable."
"This is a fine suit, armorsmith. I will be safe from harm. If only you could forge rings to mail the rest of my people . . ."
"This is a sacred duty. Master Beleren's trust has bought an eternity of my loyalty."
"This is about more than aether or inventions. Tezzeret's schemes must be stopped!"
"This is as far as I go."
"This is bigger than you. All of you."
"This is going to hurt a lot, but on the bright side, you'll be dead soon."
"This is how wars are won—not with armies of soldiers but with a single knife blade, artfully placed."
"This is just my warm-up."
"This is my place of power. Nothing can take root here unless I allow it."
"This is our land. We will not allow eyeblights to poison its beauty."
"This is the final trial! Rejoice, for the God-Pharaoh soars among us!"
"This is the forest primeval. The murmuring pines and the hemlocks . . .  Stand like Druids of old."
"This is the forest primeval. The murmuring pines and the hemlocks . . . Stand like Druids of eld."
"This is the fun part!"
"This is the light of Avacyn. Even in her absence she offers us hope."
"This is the place? This map has got to be wrong . . . ."
"This is what glory looks like."
"This is why I hate settlements. They lull you into a false sense of security."
"This is why we don't go out in banewasp weather."
"This isn't what I meant by 'facing the heat of battle!'"
"This little critter can turn all of you to scrap in under thirty seconds! Come on, who wants to be the first to go? Try and stop me!"
"This might hurt less if you don't fight so hard. But I doubt it."
"This monstrosity will do—for now."
"This new chaos confounds us. We must fling it into our winds, our storms. These we can control."
"This one has not screamed enough to show effective implantation. Kill it."
"This one is only a yearling, but it would be wise to move away before we provide it with excellent hunting practice."
"This one opens the grate outside Zelzo Base. This one is for Ismeri Library. This one is for an invisible door . . . No, I've said too much."
"This one was wearing shoes made of glass. She'll be no ordinary prey."
"This one will need direction. After all, each of its eyes is larger than its brain."
"This one's for my mom, and this one's for me."
"This party is such fun—but it's a shame to mourn just one."
"This pendant was my grandmother's legacy. I sought solitude among the trees as moonlight danced on their branches, her gift safe in my hand."
"This pestilence robs us of glorious death in battle. We starve to death with full bellies and drown trying to slake our unnatural thirst."
"This place has outlived its usefulness."
"This place suits me: craven authorities and plentiful prey."
"This research violates Consulate law."
"This scar? From a zombie's teeth. This scar? From a barbarian's axe. That scar? I don't talk about that one."
"This school was founded in secret, operates in secret, and exists for the teaching of secrets. Those who would alter reality must first escape it."
"This scum is barely worth the trouble."
"This sliver comes into the world a perfect predator. It's ready to hunt and devour its first meal within seconds of hatching."
"This soil knows well the taste of the dead. Give it the hunger for a living meal, and it can become a deadly ally."
"This sort of innovation occurs when you set out to improve an electric tea kettle and misplace a decimal."
"This species has grown to be my preferred receptacle for our divine message."
"This storm will calm. We must believe that."
"This strange new beast makes for an excellent meal. Get me more."
"This sword is Sunrise. The other is Dawn. They mark the beginning of my days but the end of yours."
"This town's only for good folk. The rest can go to the city."
"This undemanding vegetation takes root in a mote of dust but grows incredibly quickly."
"This vulgar mimicry will end now."
"This war is not about loxodon or leonin, Sylvok or Auriok. To defeat these rotters, we must do it together."
"This was quite possibly the least pleasant occurrence on the entire expedition."
"This world is a dream. We cling to our toys like children, but sooner or later we must learn to live without them."
"This world reeks of another's hand. Someone or something is defying the power of the gods and shaping this planet. I intend for it to stop."
"This world tires of its long occupation."
"This world was once so much more than the confines of Naktamun."
"This world will be ruled by its rightful sovereigns, not these hideous pretenders."
"This world will not be tamed."
"This wound shall be like the chills of winter: swiftly forgotten when spring shoots rise."
"Thorn bushes spring up wherever the army has passed. Lean years follow in the wake of a great war."
"Those Foxes are wily, swift, and ferocious. They are the warriors of the snows."
"Those blessed hands could bring surcease to even the most tainted soul."
"Those dragons grow fast. For a while they feed on squirrels and goblins and then suddenly you're missing a mammoth."
"Those idiots should never have bred Thrulls for combat!"
"Those mewling Barbarians will cower before my righteous steel!"
"Those of faith are those of strength."
"Those ogres who did not embrace oni worship were cast out, cursed, and forced into hermitage, waiting for the day the oni would come for them."
"Those talons really dig into your skin, but it's better than being dropped."
"Those who aren't welcome will know it!"
"Those who claim to know the world in its entirety rarely have the requisite perspective."
"Those who died in battle deserve their rest."
"Those who do evil and those who do nothing are equally worthy of contempt."
"Those who do not ride the wind on Aesthir still command loyalty and respect."
"Those who do not submit will be consumed."
"Those who embrace the harsh land rather than fight it find they have a powerful ally."
"Those who endure in the face of suffering, those whose faith shines long in evil days, they shall see salvation."
"Those who fear the darkness have never seen what the light can do."
"Those who fling spells too quickly should have reason to regret it."
"Those who have never ridden before the wind do not know the true joy of war."
"Those who hide in hollow towers would do well to remember the rain."
"Those who incur Thassa's anger will be swallowed whole by her waves, or torn asunder by her bident."
"Those who know do not talk. Those who talk do not know."
"Those who know only one path to victory can never hope to triumph."
"Those who live by the sword will die by the sword. I choose to do neither."
"Those who seek to upset the balance must be taxed for such ambitions."
"Those who seize power must have the means to hold it."
"Those who stood in my path now lay behind me."
"Those who think the trees shall remain bystanders throughout this conflict shall be sorely mistaken."
"Those who wish to invade our monastery, please take it up with my servant."
"Those who witness my work often question its necessity. I've never understood that."
"Those wings are no advantage. I will pin them to the ceiling of the Hekma."
"Those without beauty are Lorwyn's greatest tumor. The winnowers have an unpleasant duty, but a necessary one."
"Though I may soar, I could never fly as high as the dragons."
"Though Innistrad is not cleansed of evil, we finally have cause to rejoice."
"Though Serra has not been seen for twenty years, her Gargoyles still watch over our city and punish the guilty."
"Though in years past speculation was not encouraged about the strange ways of kami, now we must understand their motivations, if such is even possible to the mortal mind."
"Though the letter was many pages long, I could tell all I needed to know from one look at the messenger's face."
"Though the slivers may sometimes resemble us, they are not human. Anyone who fights them must remember this."
"Though there is little to be learned from your dust and stones, I shall wring them dry nevertheless."
"Though used as a piercing weapon, the tusk is more akin to a stinger, spreading pain instantly throughout the body of its victim. This specimen deserves further study."
"Though you may leave this haven we have found, may our strength never leave you."
"Thought? Deceit? Progress? Now you're just making it hungry."
"Thoughtweft binds us together as one, part of an intricate pattern that would unravel if even one thread came loose."
"Thraben is our home and I will not see it fall to this unhallowed horde."
"Thraben's pleas fall on deaf ears. Ours do not."
"Thrashes of the ancient past still linger in spirit and shadow, desperate to sink their claws into our souls."
"Thread the torsos together with angel hair to ensure they will cooperate in battle."
"Three heads, six arms, and some armor grafts are better than . . . the normal numbers of those things."
"Three such creatures stood burning at the crest of the hill. Only seconds later, the Fireball struck our front line."
"Thrice Xuande's ardent quest led to Nanyang,  Where Sleeping Dragon unveiled Han's partition: . . ."
"Through all the terrors we face, I hold on to the memory of the world before the Eldrazi came. I'd like to see that world again."
"Through me the rage of Tilonalli burns twice as bright."
"Through the haze of battle I saw the glint of sun on golden mane, the sheen of glory clad in mail, and I dropped my sword and wept at the idiocy of war."
"Through the veil's rip spilled hundreds of minor kami, rushing over the battlefield like embers from a kicked campfire. Then they were gone."
"Through your sacrifice of self, you become holy. Through your strength, all will be saved."
"Throw rocks at 'em! Throw spears at 'em! Throw Furt at 'em!"
"Thunder broke the brittle silence over the Araba. A surge of raw energy lifted the soldier's body into the air and briefly, in the heart of the flash, he saw the face of a god."
"Tideshaping is more than creating a few new puddles."
"Tie a mouse under a bridge, and your cabbages will triple in size."
"Tilonalli's searing rays carry the spark of life's eventual destruction as all light fades."
"Time and again, I have demonstrated my skills as a healer. Why, then, are you so ill at ease?"
"Time enough to become a Medic once you're hurt too badly to fight. For now, Icatia needs your strength more than your compassion."
"Time flows as the rivers do, toward an unknown sea. The wise know to look downstream."
"Time flows like a river. In Tolaria we practice the art of building dams."
"Time is a vigilant tyrant, but there are those who have broken free of its gaze."
"Time is like the Luxa River—though it flows in one direction, it can be diverted."
"Time may heal all wounds, but what heals time?"
"Time to show the foe our true mettle."
"To a creature like that, we must seem like, well, bugs."
"To a trained mind, the cold is but a momentary distraction."
"To achieve what none have achieved before, one must dare what none have dared before."
"To arms! To arms! The Lion roars!"
"To be a knight, Gideon, is to be the shield for the meek against the cruel."
"To be honest, I'm not quite sure what's going to happen."
"To break another's mind is to deliver a fate worse than death. It is a terrifying power."
"To bring her down we must be on all sides at once—leave one avenue open and we'll all be dead."
"To care for yourself, cultivate the world. To care for the world, cultivate yourself."
"To conquer is to eat."
"To control the present we must master the future."
"To create the first Thrulls, I only introduced alchemic elements into the Order's necromancy; Tourach's principles remained unchanged."
"To death all must go, and so in death lies ultimate power."
"To defeat your enemies, you must remove their ability to make war against you."
"To die failing to save a loved one is just so sad—or, more to the point, pathetic."
"To distract an archmage would take incredible power. But for a simpleton, something sparkly will do."
"To empty your mind is to fill your grave."
"To evade the brood lineages, one must be made dark to all the senses."
"To examine the causes of life, we must first have recourse to death."
"To fill your mind with knowledge, we must start by emptying it."
"To forgive our enemies is to forgive ourselves."
"To hide the truth is more than folly—it is fatal."
"To invent is to rebel."
"To make a prairie it takes a clover and one bee, One clover, and a bee, And revery."
"To make peace with the forest, make peace with me."
"To pass through the jungle: silence, courtesy, ferocity, as the occasion demands."
"To prevent action is to prevent transgression."
"To prevent, one must first predict."
"To probe the wonders of the multiverse, to gaze upon worlds unspoiled by blade or spell . . . it's enough to make one weep for the possibilities denied."
"To provoke the mountain is to invite the avalanche."
"To rise like the sun—there is no greater feeling."
"To sculpt a mind is to see every memory and thought as an individual piece that can be rearranged—or removed."
"To see gods among the people, part of their daily lives . . . It's inspiring."
"To see past the veil of death, cross it."
"To send the common people to war untrained is to throw them away."
"To show geists pity is to prolong their agonies. Whether they know it or not, they seek the Blessed Sleep, and we are to give it to them."
"To spend your life seeking, only to find regret upon achieving . . . this is the most delicious irony of all."
"To survive exceptional times we must adapt by exceptional means."
"To survive up here, I've learned when to use my harpoon and when to just enjoy the view."
"To survive, we must embrace the savagery we knew in our race's infancy."
"To survive, you must seize every opportunity."
"To the king, to the Circle, and to the realm! And to not dying."
"To the tutors, a 'poem of sand' was of little account, a 'poem of ivory,' priceless."
"To the undiscerning eye, justice and vengeance can look the same."
"To the unskilled, it appears as blurred patches of distorted light. Few have seen its true form."
"To think some believe it peaceful to die in one's sleep."
"To think that some find sleep a restful state."
"To those who can hear it, Gaea's battle song brings power as swift as sunlight and as enduring as the deep roots of the forest."
"To truly defeat a skaberen, you must destroy not the monster but the lab."
"To truly know something, you must become it. The trick is to not lose yourself in the process."
"To victory! To glory! To eternity!"
"To visit the sky requires bravery, and thought, and little else. To master the sky requires the binding of its masters, and little else."
"To wage war, secure peace within yourself."
"To-night the winds begin to rise . . . The rooks are blown about the skies . . . ."
"Today I asked Master Dosan what the ogre mages did with the humans they sacrificed. He gave me a hard look and said to think no more on the matter."
"Today the Rubblebelt is a bit larger. That's a good day's work."
"Today there is feasting and peace across our land, but the war has not ended. Tuck away your bloodlust. You'll need it tomorrow."
"Today we throw off the yoke of death. Either this is an affirmation of the eternal cyclical nature of life, or it's just hilarious—depends on which of us you ask."
"Today's paperweight, tomorrow's leveler."
"Today, for a lark, let's visit the plains. I'm sure we'll find something to entertain us."
"Together my mount and I are stronger than either of us apart."
"Together we can unlock secrets no one has even dreamed of. I might even let you remember some of them."
"Tolaria floats upon a wheel of fortune."
"Told you I had friends."
"Tonight we'll eat a farewell feast. Cold corn porridge is not enough.  Let's peel papayas, pineapples, and mangoes, drink coconut milk,  and bake bananas."
"Tonight, madam, it's your money and your life."
"Too dumb, and you end up a sibsig. Too smart, and you end up a meal. Mediocrity is the key to a long life."
"Too little, too late. The machine is in motion."
"Too many have disappeared in these dark days. I am the light that will lead them home."
"Too much friction on your bearings, your countersinking is inconsistent, and there are lines in your casting. Dispose of it, and begin again."
"Too much work—it takes a long time to break them in, and more than a few recruits."
"Torahn gore these shifty fishtails! You can't even get close to one."
"Torahn's horns! They've seen us. Now, statue, you must fight to save yourself!"
"Touch no tree, break no branch, and speak only the question you wish answered."
"Tourach's power was such that his followers deified him after his death."
"Tovolar, my master. Gather the howlpack, for the Hunter's Moon is nigh and Thraben's walls grow weak."
"Tracking a fangren pack is easy. Catching up to one is fatal."
"Trade my moose? Sure—when I find a horse that can spear ten goblins at a time!"
"Trained to battle the followers of Tourach, the Order of Leitbur was not as successful in later conflicts with Orcish and Goblin raiders."
"Training and studies aid a soldier in meager amounts. The gods do the rest."
"Training? Seeing my crops burnt to cinders was all the 'training' I needed."
"Trapmaking is an art. The trap is a corporeal riddle, a battle of wits between its creator and whatever it lures inside."
"Tread the roads of righteousness, Murat, lest you lose your way and be consumed."
"Tread too hard in the forest and it will tread on you in return."
"Tread upon the meek, and they shall wound your feet and make you crawl."
"Tread upon these flower beds at your own peril."
"Tresserhorn is ours now. Dredge the lake and bring me all the bones you find. We'll build you a new army, the likes of which Terisiare has never seen."
"Trickery can't defeat raw power."
"Troops, kitten formation! This mouse won't catch itself!"
"True intentions lie not in the head but in the heart."
